INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (492751, 'I do not believe in a fate that falls on men however they act but I do believe in a fate that falls on them unless they act. ', 63441, 0), (492752, 'Let men see, let them know, a real man, who lives as he was meant to live.', 267, 0), (492753, 'Give to everyone who begs from you; and of him who takes away your goods do not ask them again. And as you wish that men would do to you, do so to them.', 17018, 0), (492754, 'Only free men can negotiate. A prisoner cannot enter into contracts.', 1722, 0), (492755, 'Brave men do not gather by thousands to torture and murder a single individual, so gagged and bound he cannot make even feeble resistance or defense.', 71385, 0), (492756, 'An American monkey, after getting drunk on brandy, would never touch it again, and thus is much wiser than most men.', 1024, 0), (492757, 'They talk like angels but they live like men.', 62829, 0), (492758, 'The greatest enemy to human souls is the self-righteous spirit which makes men look to themselves for salvation.', 36532, 0), (492759, 'I am not a hero but the brave men who died deserved this honor.', 75892, 0), (492760, 'The superior man is distressed by the limitations of his ability he is not distressed by the fact that men do not recognize the ability that he has. ', 819, 0), (492761, 'The true test of a man''s style is the haircut. There are some men who look good no matter how their hair is styled, whether it''s trendy or not. A man can change his haircut many times, but to pull off any haircut, you have to be very chic. Like Brad Pitt.', 67000, 0), (492762, 'All free men, wherever they may live, are citizens of Berlin. And therefore, as a free man, I take pride in the words ''Ich bin ein Berliner!''', 1680, 0), (492763, 'The child often sees only what he already knows. He projects the whole of his verbal thought into things. He sees mountains as built by men, rivers as dug out with spades, the sun and moon as following us on our walks.', 9651, 0), (492764, 'Men in general are quick to believe that which they wish to be true.', 62623, 0), (492765, 'The reason why men enter into society is the preservation of their property.', 2375, 0), (492766, 'Men are so simple and so much inclined to obey immediate needs that a deceiver will never lack victims for his deceptions.', 947, 0), (492767, 'We sleep safe in our beds because rough men stand ready in the night to visit violence on those who would do us harm.', 521, 0), (492768, 'The vote is the most powerful instrument ever devised by man for breaking down injustice and destroying the terrible walls which imprison men because they are different from other men.', 1763, 0), (492769, 'The mass of men lead lives of quiet desperation. What is called resignation is confirmed desperation.', 1049, 0), (492770, 'Some people think having large breasts makes a woman stupid. Actually, it''s quite the opposite: a woman having large breasts makes men stupid.', 2210, 0), (492771, 'The less men think, the more they talk.', 48659, 0), (492772, 'Landlords, like all other men, love to reap where they never sowed.', 1336, 0), (492773, 'It does not take great men to do great things it only takes consecrated men. ', 22130, 0), (492774, 'While civilization has been improving our houses, it has not equally improved the men who are to inhabit them. It has created palaces, but it was not so easy to create noblemen and kings.', 1049, 0), (492775, 'I am looking for a lot of men who have an infinite capacity to not know what can''t be done.', 1796, 0), (492776, 'There is no justice among men.', 66581, 0), (492777, 'Make no little plans they have no magic to stir men''s blood and probably themselves will not be realized. ', 67346, 0), (492778, 'The mountains, the forest, and the sea, render men savage; they develop the fierce, but yet do not destroy the human.', 98, 0), (492779, 'Men may be popular without being ambitious, but there is hardly an ambitious man who