5, 0), (492841, 'Children will always be afraid of the dark, and men with minds sensitive to hereditary impulse will always tremble at the thought of the hidden and fathomless worlds of strange life which may pulsate in the gulfs beyond the stars, or press hideously upon our own globe in unholy dimensions which only the dead and the moonstruck can glimpse.', 1060, 0), (492842, 'If a man has talent and can''t use it, he''s failed. If he uses only half of it, he has partly failed. If he uses the whole of it, he has succeeded, and won a satisfaction and triumph few men ever know.', 1971, 0), (492843, 'I shall never be a heretic; I may err in dispute, but I do not wish to decide anything finally; on the other hand, I am not bound by the opinions of men.', 1746, 0), (492844, 'Men freely believe that which they desire.', 62623, 0), (492845, 'As a young boy, I was obsessed with endangered species and the extinct species that men killed off. Biology was the subject in school that I was incredibly passionate about.', 68700, 0), (492846, 'The graveyards are full of indispensable men.', 11599, 0), (492847, 'A man is ethical only when life, as such, is sacred to him, that of plants and animals as that of his fellow men, and when he devotes himself helpfully to all life that is in need of help.', 1006, 0), (492848, 'There are only two kinds of men: the righteous who think they are sinners and the sinners who think they are righteous.', 144, 0), (492849, 'Men may die, but the fabrics of free institutions remains unshaken.', 66663, 0), (492850, 'How could man rejoice in victory and delight in the slaughter of men?', 15, 0);
