INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493101, 'I don''t usually lose my temper, but if I get angry, it''s true - I''m scary.', 75898, 0), (493102, 'Anger and intolerance are the enemies of correct understanding.', 32, 0), (493103, 'It is wise to direct your anger towards problems - not people to focus your energies on answers - not excuses. ', 1820, 0), (493104, 'Silence is one of the hardest arguments to refute.', 3355, 0), (493105, 'I shall allow no man to belittle my soul by making me hate him.', 5998, 0), (493106, 'When angry, count to four; when very angry, swear.', 286, 0), (493107, 'There''s a natural law of karma that vindictive people, who go out of their way to hurt others, will end up broke and alone.', 35699, 0), (493108, 'Whatever is begun in anger ends in shame.', 1077, 0), (493109, 'When angry count to ten before you speak. If very angry, count to one hundred.', 1207, 0), (493110, 'Depression, suffering and anger are all part of being human.', 524, 0), (493111, 'For me, comedy starts as a spew, a kind of explosion, and then you sculpt it from there, if at all. It comes out of a deeper, darker side. Maybe it comes from anger, because I''m outraged by cruel absurdities, the hypocrisy that exists everywhere, even within yourself, where it''s hardest to see.', 2185, 0), (493112, 'Yesterday, we fought wars which destroyed cities. Today, we are concerned with avoiding a war which will destroy the earth. We can adapt atomic energy to produce electricity and move ships, but can we control its use in anger?', 60667, 0), (493113, 'A man that studieth revenge keeps his own wounds green.', 1035, 0), (493114, 'The opposite of anger is not calmness, its empathy.', 72135, 0), (493115, 'I have sadness in me. I have anger in me. I have heartbreak in me.', 1217, 0), (493116, 'The ignorant mind, with its infinite afflictions, passions, and evils, is rooted in the three poisons. Greed, anger, and delusion.', 14298, 0), (493117, 'When I am angry I can pray well and preach well.', 1746, 0), (493118, 'One of man''s greatest obligations is anger.', 1048, 0), (493119, 'Guilt is anger directed at ourselves - at what we did or did not do. Resentment is anger directed at others - at what they did or did not do.', 30410, 0), (493120, 'Anger is like a storm rising up from the bottom of your consciousness. When you feel it coming, turn your focus to your breath.', 394, 0), (493121, 'Anger dwells only in the bosom of fools.', 104, 0), (493122, 'When a man points a finger at someone else, he should remember that four of his fingers are pointing at himself.', 31146, 0), (493123, 'Generally speaking, if a human being never shows anger, then I think something''s wrong. He''s not right in the brain.', 5025, 0), (493124, 'As a human being, anger is a part of our mind. Irritation also part of our mind. But you can do - anger come, go. Never keep in your sort of - your inner world, then create a lot of suspicion, a lot of distrust, a lot of negative things, more worry.', 5025, 0), (493125, 'Anger is never without a reason, but seldom with a good one.', 1077, 0), (493126, 'Good satire comes from anger. It comes from a sense of injustice, that there are wrongs in the world that need to be fixed. And what better place to get that well of venom and outrage boiling than a newsroom, because you''re on the front lines.', 2257, 0), (493127, 'I think everybody should have the same anger towards the injustice that''s happening and the hatred that''s happening, and just fight it with love and compassion.', 1217, 0), (493128, 'Words, especially when yelled in anger, can be very damaging to a child''s self-confidence. The child probably already feels bad enough just from seeing the consequences of his or her behavior. Our sons and daughters don''t need more guilt and self-doubt heaped upon their already wounded egos.', 1834, 0), (493129, 'Getting angry doesn''t solve anything.', 11920, 0), (493130, 'Heaven has no rage like love to hatred turned, nor hell a fury like a woman scorned.', 14081, 0), (493131, 'When one burns one''s bridges, what a very nice fire it makes.', 300, 0), (493132, 'Don''t get the impression that you arouse my anger. You see, one can only be angry with those he respects.', 9695, 0), (493133, 'The flame of anger, bright and brief, sharpens the barb of love.', 8764, 0), (493134, 'I always channeled what I felt emotionally into skiing - my insecurities, my anger, my disappointment. Skiing was always my outlet, and it worked.', 68105, 0), (493135, 'I do stand up sometimes out of anger. Sometimes the greatest stuff comes from a dark place.', 68238, 0), (493136, 'He who angers you conquers you.', 63752, 0), (493137, 'You feel the shame, humiliation, and anger at being just another victim of prejudice, and at the same time, there''s the nagging worry that maybe... you''re just no good.', 19782, 0), (493138, 'We boil at different degrees.', 2269, 0), (493139, 'Get mad, then get over it.', 1749, 0), (493140, 'A man that does not know how to be angry does not know how to be good.', 2175, 0), (493141, 'Anger is a killing thing: it kills the man who angers, for each rage leaves him less than he had been before - it takes something from him.', 1682, 0), (493142, 'There is nothing that so much gratifies an ill tongue as when it finds an angry heart.', 1348, 0), (493143, 'Indulge not thyself in the passion of anger; it is whetting a sword to wound thine own breast, or murder thy friend.', 43279, 0), (493144, 'As you get older, you see the world at a different angle, maybe more cynically, but I just bury my anger.', 51830, 0), (493145, 'Denial, panic, threats, anger - those are very human responses to feeling guilt.', 68282, 0), (493146, 'Con men look for human frailty to exploit. This is most often greed. Trump found a different vice: anger. The emotional are always the most susceptible to manipulation.', 73298, 0), (493147, 'If you get down and quarell everyday, you''re saying prayers to the devil, I say.', 7, 0), (493148, 'It seems to me that election season is just a Petri dish for anger and cynicism.', 86, 0), (493149, 'The one who cannot restrain their anger will wish undone, what their temper and irritation prompted them to do.', 2542, 0), (493150, 'Revenge is often like biting a dog because the dog bit you.', 36106, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493151, 'Sometimes it''s worse to win a fight than to lose.', 9623, 0), (493152, 'Anger makes dull men witty, but it keeps them poor.', 1035, 0), (493153, 'Be calm in arguing; for fierceness makes error a fault, and truth discourtesy.', 3428, 0), (493154, 'A broken bone can heal, but the wound a word opens can fester forever.', 3164, 0), (493155, 'The best remedy for a short temper is a long walk.', 8895, 0), (493156, 'Behind every argument is someone''s ignorance.', 16727, 0), (493157, 'Anger, if not restrained, is frequently more hurtful to us than the injury that provokes it.', 65434, 0), (493158, 'Anger is a wind which blows out the lamp of the mind.', 67335, 0), (493159, 'There was never an angry man that thought his anger unjust.', 63291, 0), (493160, 'Reacting in anger or annoyance will not advance one''s ability to persuade.', 28287, 0), (493161, 'Do not meddle in the affairs of Wizards, for they are subtle and quick to anger.', 65, 0), (493162, 'I did not want to put myself on the line, as an Australian playing Britain''s greatest comic actor. The fans of Sellers are obsessive, possessive - and aggressive. I did not want to risk their anger - or my own reputation.', 72311, 0), (493163, 'Anger is a manifestation of a deeper issue... and that, for me, is based on insecurity, self-esteem and loneliness.', 27363, 0), (493164, 'I''ve always turned my anger inwards towards self-destruction.', 74823, 0), (493165, 'I''m generally slow to anger, quick to forgive, and I take in information before making decisions. So no matter how controversial the decision, my general demeanour is to put on white lab coat and gloves and look at the evidence, weigh the arguments and see what makes sense.', 75899, 0), (493166, 'When you hold on to anger and unforgiveness, you can''t move forward.', 47442, 0), (493167, 'Sometimes the routes leading to feelings of anger are so convoluted and circuitous that it takes enormous skill to discern their original source, or fountainhead. But regardless of the reason for or the source of the anger or the relative ease or complexity in perceiving either the anger or its source - everybody, but everybody, gets angry.', 65610, 0), (493168, 'President Obama and members of his administration constantly express rage and anger over events totally within their control. It''s an odd and unsettling fact of American life that so many Americans seem to think that such expressions of frustration should substitute for actual competence.', 17797, 0), (493169, 'Vengeance is the act of turning anger in on yourself. On the surface it may be directed at someone else, but it is a surefire recipe for arresting emotional recovery.', 74441, 0), (493170, 'Each person''s drive to overwork is unique, and doing too much numbs every workaholic''s emotions differently. Sometimes overwork numbs depression, sometimes anger, sometimes envy, sometimes sexuality. Or the overworker runs herself ragged in a race for attention.', 18332, 0), (493171, 'I don''t feel bitterness, I don''t feel anger towards anybody. Fighting is never emotional to me.', 56476, 0), (493172, 'I''m very much inspired by things that anger me. If I see bigotry, stupidity, or injustice on the news, I''m inspired to find a way to make it into something comedic and relatable. Anger inspires me. Stupidity inspires me. My family inspires me. My accountant inspires me. Everything and anything, really.', 68025, 0), (493173, 'Violent anger makes me physically ill.', 1009, 0), (493174, 'My songs have always been frustrating themes, relationships that I''ve had. And now that I''m in love, I expect it to be really happy, or at least there won''t be half as much anger as there was.', 890, 0), (493175, 'The ego mind both professes its desire for love and does everything possible to repel it, or if it gets here anyway, to sabotage it. That is why dealing with issues like control, anger, and neediness is the most important work in preparing ourselves for love.', 534, 0), (493176, 'In plain terms, a child is a complicated creature who can drive you crazy. There''s a cruelty to childhood, there''s an anger.', 585, 0), (493177, 'I think my passion is misinterpreted as anger sometimes. And I don''t think people are ready for the message that I''m delivering, and delivering with a sense of violent love.', 23240, 0), (493178, 'The spiritual message is we lose our lives in pleasing others; if you''re the good child who pleases Mommy and Daddy but internalizes anger, you''re setting yourself up for disease.', 64551, 0), (493179, 'Anger is an unnecessary emotion. Loads of stuff in life can trigger it, but what matters is how you react. I choose not to react.', 73075, 0), (493180, 'Anger is just not who I am, and I don''t think it''s what voters in the 6th district want. They want respectful, decent representation that contrasts so starkly with what we have in Washington.', 75900, 0), (493181, 'It''s important to remember that the animals are not grieving with us. They''re very accepting. They''re not lying there thinking ''How could you do this to me? Why aren''t you keeping me going?'' Pets don''t do the human things of guilt and anger and recrimination that we do. They come and go with great acceptance.', 63, 0), (493182, 'Let there be a door to thy mouth, that it may be shut when need arises, and let it be carefully barred, that none may rouse thy voice to anger, and thou pay back abuse with abuse.', 69072, 0), (493183, 'My anger with the US was not at first, that they had used that weapon - although that anger came later.', 68690, 0), (493184, 'I want to express myself to feel that what I feel is real. My joy, my pain, my anger.', 69986, 0), (493185, 'I started writing because there''s an absence of things I was familiar with or that I dreamed about. One of my senses of anger is related to this vacancy - a yearning I had as a teenager... and when I get ready to write, I think I''m trying to fill that.', 8628, 0), (493186, 'People are fed up with the way things are. There is a lot of bitterness out there, a lot of anger about a lack of jobs and concerns for the next generation.', 69667, 0), (493187, 'Love implies anger. The man who is angered by nothing cares about nothing.', 1370, 0), (493188, 'Every time you get angry, you poison your own system.', 877, 0), (493189, 'He who is incapable of feeling strong passions, of being shaken by anger, of living in every sense of the word, will never be a good actor.', 64168, 0), (493190, 'No one''s banging down my door. People see the way I look, and they don''t feel threatened, but they should watch out for me. They don''t know there''s a steel rod that drives me. I get ticked off, and the rage just gets me going. My motor is anger.', 37938, 0), (493191, 'Somebody hits me, I''m going to hit him back. Even if it does look like he hasn''t eaten in a while.', 15009, 0), (493192, 'We''re comfortable with women in certain roles but not comfortable with women expressing anger or fully accepting their power. The most daring question a woman can ask is, ''What do I want?''', 798, 0), (493193, 'Wars spring from unseen and generally insignificant causes, the first outbreak being often but an explosion of anger.', 2096, 0), (493194, 'I don''t think your ability to fight has anything to do with how big you are. It''s to do with how much anger is in you.', 11891, 0), (493195, 'One of the most interesting things about the cognitive theory is the idea that anger and interpersonal conflict ultimately result from a mental con. In other words, you''re telling yourself things that aren''t entirely true when you''re fighting with someone.', 11168, 0), (493196, 'I think Donald Trump taps into an anger that I hear every day. People are angry that a commonsense thing like securing the border or ending sanctuary cities is somehow considered extreme. It''s not extreme it''s common sense. We need to secure the border. ', 66662, 0), (493197, 'When you are offended at any man''s fault, turn to yourself and study your own failings. Then you will forget your anger.', 1328, 0), (493198, 'Extremism thrives amid ignorance and anger, intimidation and cowardice.', 66567, 0), (493199, 'Anger begins with folly, and ends with repentance.', 464, 0), (493200, 'A man must fortify himself and understand that a wise man who yields to laziness or anger or passion or love of drink, or who commits any other action prompted by impulse and inopportune, will probably find his fault condoned; but if he stoops to greed, he will not be pardoned, but render himself odious as a combination of all vices at once.', 72615, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493201, 'My father was so very afraid. I felt it in the sting of his black leather belt, which he applied with more anxiety than anger, my father who beat me as if someone might steal me away, because that was exactly what was happening all around us.', 1309, 0), (493202, 'I''ve chosen my wedding ring large and heavy to continue forever. But exactly because of that all the time that Dave and I have an argument I feel it like handcuffs, and on anger time I throw it in a basket. Poor Dave, he bought me three wedding rings already!', 75901, 0), (493203, 'In the heat of our campaigns, we have all become accustomed to a little anger and exaggeration. Yet, on the whole, our political process has served us well.', 75902, 0), (493204, 'Take the high road. No matter how much strife, and consternation, frustration and anger you might be confronted with - don''t go to that level.', 20172, 0), (493205, 'As long as anger, paranoia and misinformation drive our political debate, there are unhinged souls among us who will feel justified in turning to violent remedies for imagined threats.', 67465, 0), (493206, 'I am ready to accept all accusations, allegations, anger - but I have to succeed.', 75903, 0), (493207, 'The intoxication of anger, like that of the grape, shows us to others, but hides us from ourselves.', 8695, 0), (493208, 'Anger is as a stone cast into a wasp''s nest.', 3779, 0), (493209, 'Anger can be a problem, but it has tremendous potential, too. It''s just figuring out what to do with it.', 3185, 0), (493210, 'You know how big love is? Love is big. love can hold anger love can even hold hatred. ', 753, 0), (493211, 'I was filled with hate and anger. But during my trial, something decisive happened: Amnesty International adopted me as a prisoner of conscience, and it was an unbelievable feeling to know that there is someone fighting for you on the outside. Amnesty''s ''soft'' approach made me seriously consider alternatives to revenge.', 10487, 0), (493212, 'It isn''t enough just to scream at the Occupy Wall Street demonstrations. We need our political system to start reflect this anger back into, ''How do we fix it? How do we get the economy going again?''', 1749, 0), (493213, 'Freedom of expression is tested during times of anger and conflict and enables all opinions and outraged expressions of dissent that we may not want to hear. But even for this there have to be limits.', 71243, 0), (493214, 'Arguments only confirm people in their own opinions.', 15847, 0), (493215, 'You want to see an angry person? Let me hear a cell phone go off.', 72138, 0), (493216, 'The poor monkey, quietly seated on the ground, seemed to be in sore trouble at this display of anger.', 33112, 0), (493217, 'I think people should be angry at things that are worthy of anger. Injustice is outrageous and deserves outrage.', 17785, 0), (493218, 'The injunction to be nice is used to deflect criticism and stifle the legitimate anger of dissent.', 1833, 0), (493219, 'Anger will never disappear so long as thoughts of resentment are cherished in the mind. Anger will disappear just as soon as thoughts of resentment are forgotten.', 8695, 0), (493220, 'Anger is like those ruins which smash themselves on what they fall.', 65434, 0), (493221, 'There''s a lot of bitterness, there''s a lot of anger out there. We all have to work hard to heal those wounds.', 74175, 0), (493222, 'A little anger is a good thing if it isn''t on your own behalf, if it''s for others deserving of your anger, your empathy.', 28866, 0), (493223, 'When I was younger, I was terrified to express anger because it would often kick-start a horrible reaction in the men in my life. So I bit my tongue. I was left to painstakingly deal with the aftermath of my avoidance later in life, in therapy or through the lyrics of my songs.', 21687, 0), (493224, 'I had a trainer during ''Spiderman,'' and I discovered I have deep-seated rage when I''m holding heavy weights over my head. Whatever dormant anger I have in me, that''s where it comes out. That''s not the kind of working out I want to do.', 13298, 0), (493225, 'Relationships based on deals between leaders or ruling elites tend to collapse amid popular anger.', 67849, 0), (493226, 'I grew up here, and it''s always been a very diverse community. So for people to come out and say that there''s some long-standing anger or there''s a history of racial tension is absolutely ridiculous. There''s not a black-white divide in Ferguson.', 75904, 0), (493227, 'Anger can be a useful emotion; it''s built into our genetic code to help with self preservation. But it can also be destructive, even when it is justified.', 71237, 0), (493228, 'I don''t think it''s good to run on anger, but it''s really great when that''s the first couple of gallons in your tank - when you''ve had enough, and you''re just pissed off enough to go for it. In a lot of ways, that sort of environment can be a catapult for a great situation.', 20120, 0), (493229, 'I have a right to my anger, and I don''t want anybody telling me I shouldn''t be, that it''s not nice to be, and that something''s wrong with me because I get angry.', 68737, 0), (493230, 'Every child senses, with all the horse sense that''s in him, that any parent is angry inside when children misbehave and they dread more the anger that is rarely or never expressed openly, wondering how awful it might be.', 2463, 0), (493231, 'Never do anything when you are in a temper, for you will do everything wrong.', 1255, 0), (493232, 'The world needs anger. The world often continues to allow evil because it isn''t angry enough.', 25253, 0), (493233, 'Anger is a momentary madness, so control your passion or it will control you.', 55680, 0), (493234, 'No man can think clearly when his fists are clenched.', 6546, 0), (493235, 'Anger is a short madness.', 2542, 0), (493236, 'My father was often angry when I was most like him.', 1991, 0), (493237, 'Anger cannot be dishonest.', 267, 0), (493238, 'One should not lose one''s temper unless one is certain of getting more and more angry to the end.', 62867, 0), (493239, 'What starts the process, really, are laughs and slights and snubs when you are a kid. If your anger is deep enough and strong enough, you learn that you can change those attitudes by excellence, personal gut performance.', 9695, 0), (493240, 'Wise anger is like fire from a flint: there is great ado to get it out; and when it does come, it is out again immediately.', 31769, 0), (493241, 'Anger may repast with thee for an hour, but not repose for a night; the continuance of anger is hatred, the continuance of hatred turns malice.', 4935, 0), (493242, 'I know, to banish anger altogether from one''s breast is a difficult task. It cannot be achieved through pure personal effort. It can be done only by God''s grace.', 32, 0), (493243, 'Anger and hate against one we love steels our hearts, but contempt or pity leaves us silent and ashamed.', 6974, 0), (493244, 'Although you may spend your life killing, You will not exhaust all your foes. But if you quell your own anger, your real enemy will be slain.', 10134, 0), (493245, 'Life is precious and there''s not a lot of room for anger.', 34619, 0), (493246, 'Generalised anger and frustration is something that gets you in the studio, and gets you to work - though it''s not necessarily evident in anything that''s finished.', 75905, 0), (493247, 'It is typical of women to fester and ferment over disappointments, slights, annoyances, angers, etc.', 12362, 0), (493248, 'In general I was a good kid. It usually took a lot to make me mad. But once I reached the boiling point, I lost all rational control. Totally without thinking, when my anger was aroused, I grabbed the nearest brick, rock, or stick to bash someone. It was as if I had no conscious will in the matter.', 1793, 0), (493249, 'I don''t have the feeling of being motivated by anger, revenge or frustration.', 71689, 0), (493250, 'So many women keep their anger inside and let it build until they explode and then people blow them off again.', 71125, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493251, 'Successful prime-time television of any genre produces some kind of emotional reaction in the viewers. There are a lot of different emotions to tap into. The emotion of the reward of discovery, the feeling of righteous anger, the feelings of pathos and sadness, or sentimentality of being moved by something.', 17785, 0), (493252, 'I originally wanted to embrace the imagery and forthrightness of rap music. There are some interesting, dynamic voices in rap. But I find most of it irresponsible in its overt violence and commercialization of anger. As artists, we believe we can will action through language. If that''s the case, we have to take responsibility for what we say.', 8821, 0), (493253, 'It angers me when sustainability gets used as a buzz word. For 90 percent of the world, sustainability is a matter of survival.', 66631, 0), (493254, 'Whether one admired or was repulsed by the positions he took on matters foreign and domestic, it is undeniable that Reagan''s ability to project anger was highly attractive to his most passionate supporters on the far right - and crucial to his political success.', 28560, 0), (493255, 'Books are in no hurry. An act of creation is in no hurry; it reads us, it privileges us infinitely. The notion that it is the occasion for our cleverness fills me with baffled bitterness and anger.', 2646, 0), (493256, 'To find gratitude and generosity when you could reasonably find hurt and resentment will surprise you. It will be so surprising because you will see so much of the opposite: people who have much more than others yet who react with anger when one advantage is lost or with resentment when an added gift is denied.', 9158, 0), (493257, 'The emotions in a song - the anger, aggression - have got to be legitimate.', 392, 0), (493258, 'There''s very little dislike of Americans in the world, shown by repeated polls, and the dissatisfaction - that is, the hatred and the anger - they come from acceptance of American values, not a rejection of them, and recognition that they''re rejected by the U.S. government and by U.S. elites, which does lead to hatred and anger.', 1955, 0), (493259, 'Since the day I was born, wrestling has sustained me and my family. It''s the way my father fed me; it''s the way I feed my kids. More importantly, wrestling is my greatest release. It''s been such a blessing for me. I can step into the ring and let it all go - all my anger, all my frustration, all my pain.', 75906, 0), (493260, 'Self-pity, a dominant characteristic of sociopaths, is also the characteristic that differentiates heroic storytelling from psychological rumination. When you talk about your experiences to shed light, you may feel wrenching pain, grief, anger, or shame. Your audience may pity you, but not because you want them to.', 29471, 0), (493261, 'Your emotions are exposed when you play golf: humility, pride, anger, it all comes out with each swing. You lay it all on the line.', 75907, 0), (493262, 'I don''t like greed, I don''t like ignorance. I really don''t like anger. But I love love.', 9448, 0), (493263, 'Anger is energising. The opposite of anger is depression, which is anger turned inward.', 1739, 0), (493264, 'Being irrational and out of control is what happens in real life. Not cautiously choreographing your anger or your emotions, losing yourself in them is what happens in real life.', 68181, 0), (493265, 'I think I have a normal threshold of anger, but it''s true that I am, by nature, belligerent.', 2074, 0), (493266, 'Maybe it''s stress or anger or adrenaline or disillusionment or a bullying nature or simple fear of getting killed themselves, but there is a problem if a cop cannot tell the difference between a menacing gangster and the far more common person they encounter whose life is a little frayed and messy.', 67465, 0), (493267, 'The idea that the law should punish what is rude; that government should protect our tender sensibilities from those who would - quite often with shallow motivations but sometimes with deeper and more serious complaints - challenge our national certainties and rituals, should alarm and anger us.', 2631, 0), (493268, 'I am not deaf. I hear the anger. I see the dissatisfaction, and I have to go faster.', 67005, 0), (493269, 'What''s often not acknowledged about depression is how much anger is in it.', 68863, 0), (493270, 'If you''re with a close friend, your anger may raise his blood pressure as well as your own, whereas loving feelings may lower blood pressure in both of you.', 45749, 0), (493271, 'I feel truth, beauty, love, grief, anger, intimacy & alive in my body... Women in the global south live in their bodies much more than we in the global north. Not as distracted by patriarchy''s controlling images - They know power is in their bodies. I am deeply grateful for the women who showed me the way home.', 71407, 0), (493272, 'There is a latent anger in a lot of people that went to boarding school at an early age. I was eight. And I loved it over the five years, but I think the adjustments for eight-year-olds are a lot. And I think it informs who you are for a long, long time.', 67015, 0), (493273, 'So many people live with anger and unforgiveness, and many of them are Christians.', 1206, 0), (493274, 'You have to understand the Newark Riots - a lot of people understand that the pain was the initial explosion of anger and alienation, but after that, the response, sending the National Guard troops - a lot of violence was carried out and perpetrated by those who were allegedly coming here to protect residents.', 10615, 0), (493275, 'When you fight, anger drives up testosterone in both men and women.', 52746, 0), (493276, 'In many ways, anger is a misdirected plea for love.', 5238, 0), (493277, 'Anger, if used properly, might be for a cause, like helping feed children or stopping abuse somewhere. When we understand that every quality has importance and value, then we open up to this. Shining a light on these shadow qualities gives it balance.', 5671, 0), (493278, 'The world in general doesn''t know what to make of originality; it is startled out of its comfortable habits of thought, and its first reaction is one of anger.', 235, 0), (493279, 'I would be pleased if someone would invent a pill to remove my impatience, moodiness, and occasional bursts of anger. But if they did, I wouldn''t be able to write my novels or paint.', 128, 0), (493280, 'Public anger over bank bailouts was as much about fairness as the billions of dollars spent.', 61422, 0), (493281, 'The Occupy movement found places where people who were feeling that anger could come and share it - and that is, as we all know, extremely important in any political movement. The Occupy sites became a way you could gauge the levels of anger and discontent.', 535, 0), (493282, 'Christ hath instituted Baptism as a bath, to wash away the anger, and hath put into us the Noble Stone, viz. the water of eternal life, for an earnest-penny, so that instantly in our childhood we might be able to escape the wrath.', 5825, 0), (493283, 'Like the marriage contract you entered into, your divorce is a legal transaction. Treat it that way. Try not to let emotion, hurt, fear or anger dictate the circumstances of your discussions or negotiations.', 74221, 0), (493284, 'Deep down, my mom had long suspected I was gay... Much of her anger and hurt came from her sense of betrayal that she was the last to be told.', 72234, 0), (493285, 'Violence is a problem we all want to solve. I want to make sure that kids learn to deal with anger by learning how to talk with people to solve problems. Here in the United States Senate I want to make sure we have safe schools, safe neighborhoods and good things for kids to do after school!', 72566, 0), (493286, 'That feeds anger, and I mean when we went and at last thank heavens got towards peace in Northern Ireland we went for justice within Northern Ireland as well as using security well, as well as a political settlement, but surely that is the lesson.', 68793, 0), (493287, 'Imagine a thousand more such daily intrusions in your life, every hour and minute of every day, and you can grasp the source of this paranoia, this anger that could consume me at any moment if I lost control.', 45707, 0), (493288, 'Fantastic tyrant of the amorous heart. How hard thy yoke, how cruel thy dart. Those escape your anger who refuse your sway, and those are punished most, who most obey.', 7402, 0), (493289, 'The death of Garang has unfortunately unleashed emotions of anger; some genuine, others cultivated by elements who wanted to pit one group of Sudanese against another.', 75908, 0), (493290, 'All I do is have fun. When I''m not working, it''s about making people laugh. I love making jokes about things. Even when someone''s mad at me, I''ll deflect anger with humor. My days are filled with laughter. If I''m not laughing, I''m not happy.', 75909, 0), (493291, 'Anger is implanted in us as sort of sting, to make us gnash with our teeth against the devil, to make us vehement against him, not to set us in array against each other.', 66116, 0), (493292, 'When anger rushes unrestrained to action, like a hot steed, it stumbles on its way. The man of thought strikes deepest and strikes safely.', 66116, 0), (493293, 'I think, often, when you are in just a lot of pain, it comes out as anger.', 75910, 0), (493294, 'To anger female voters in America is to tread on the tiger''s tail. Women turn out in huge numbers, and they are well aware of how their bodies work and what they need.', 68, 0), (493295, 'People are always angry at America. They''re absolutely certain that America either caused their problems or is deliberately not fixing their problems. But the anger is always directed at America and never at Americans.', 10731, 0), (493296, 'Abstract anger is great for rhetorical carrying on. You can go on endlessly about the post office, but it doesn''t mean you''re mad at your mailman.', 10731, 0), (493297, 'In Israel, waves of anger and fear circulate all the time, but so do jokes and gossip and silky evening breezes. So, too, in America.', 10731, 0), (493298, 'Obama and his attack dogs have nothing but hate and anger in their hearts and spew it whenever possible.', 64643, 0), (493299, 'A large part of mankind is angry not with the sins, but with the sinners.', 65434, 0), (493300, 'The deferring of anger is the best antidote to anger.', 65434, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493301, 'I think that to acknowledge a new generation is to acknowledge some degree of obsolescence in yourself, and that is very hard to do and often comes with undeniable anger.', 1002, 0), (493302, 'Chekhov was capable of casually tossing off deplorable comments in his letters, combined with a very modern anger against anti-Semitism.', 408, 0), (493303, 'I''ve had no problem harnessing anger.', 2269, 0), (493304, 'To me, it''s OK to have differences. But we don''t have to be mad about it. You know? And I think that''s where sometimes we get so passionate that we - you know, it turns into anger.', 3956, 0), (493305, 'Hatred is inveterate anger.', 1306, 0), (493306, 'Hatred is settled anger.', 1306, 0), (493307, 'There''s nothing wrong with anger provided you use it constructively.', 21729, 0), (493308, 'There''s a lot of anger in the Twitter-verse, as I''ve discovered. But there''s a lot of love.', 1099, 0), (493309, 'My first reaction every time I delve into an episode of history that I don''t know very much about is... my first reaction is anger that my teachers never taught me about it.', 5194, 0), (493310, 'Listen, Bruce Lee fought out of anger. That''s why they call it the ''Fists of Fury.'' Michael Jackson danced with fury. I do stand up out of fury. I''m not mad at anybody. I''m not mad at any human being because I''m a human being.', 68238, 0), (493311, 'Anger is certainly a kind of baseness, as it appears well in the weakness of those subjects in whom it reigns: children, women, old folks, sick folks.', 1035, 0), (493312, 'My own approach has always been to push intense emotions down and attempt to deal with them later. When I was younger, I was terrified to express anger because it would often kick-start a horrible reaction in the men in my life.', 21687, 0), (493313, 'When someone says that I''m angry it''s actually a compliment. I have not always been direct with my anger in my relationships, which is part of why I''d write about it in my songs because I had such fear around expressing anger as a woman.', 21687, 0), (493314, 'It''s a joke to think that anyone is one thing. We''re all such complex creatures. But if I''m going to be a poster child for anything, anger''s a gorgeous emotion. It gets a bad rap, but it can make great changes happen.', 21687, 0), (493315, 'What influenced me was Tori Amos, who was unapologetic about expressing anger through music, and Sinead O''Connor. Those two in particular were really moving for me, and very inspiring, before I wrote ''Jagged Little Pill.''', 21687, 0), (493316, 'Anger has been a really big deal for women: how can we express it without feeling that, as the physically weaker sex, we won''t get killed. The alpha-woman was burned at the stake and had her head chopped off in days of old.', 21687, 0), (493317, 'Pundits talk about ''populist rage'' as a way to trivialize the anger and fear coursing through the middle class.', 23090, 0), (493318, 'I do have anger management issues. Not clinical. Probably no more than most people.', 69023, 0), (493319, 'My therapist says I still haven''t got in touch with my anger. Maybe one day I''m going to explode. But I''m still really happy. I know it looks like a strange and painful upbringing - all those experiences led me to the paths that I''m on now.', 292, 0), (493320, 'Fighting in the ring or cage is very much different from fighting in the street. Fighting in the street is very much fueled by anger, pride, and male dominance and ego.', 67004, 0), (493321, 'Anger is wonderful. It keeps you going. I''m angry about bankers. About the government.', 195, 0), (493322, 'President Obama clearly cannot run on his record. All he''s offering is more of the same. That''s not good. Look at the economy. It''s stagnating. And so, what they''re now going to try and do is bring this campaign down to little things, distractions, distortions, smear, fear, anger, frustration.', 66572, 0), (493323, 'I''m not someone who feels anger on particular issues.', 68838, 0), (493324, 'The sense of anger I had when I was younger is something I thought would never go away. Over time, it''s something you get almost bored with.', 49828, 0), (493325, 'I turned to music originally because of my past and needing a release or an outlet to get out anger or frustration or hurt.', 11155, 0), (493326, 'I''m very much aware of the dangers of becoming a cliche. Mr. Anger, someone who gets meaner, angrier on record.', 60178, 0), (493327, 'Emotional life grows out of an area of the brain called the limbic system, specifically the amygdala, whence come delight and disgust and fear and anger.', 36805, 0), (493328, 'Hatred is an affair of the heart contempt that of the head. ', 1304, 0), (493329, 'Until recently, we regarded love as supernatural. We were willing to study the brain chemistry of fear and depression and anger but not love.', 52746, 0), (493330, 'First and foremost, we need to be the adults we want our children to be. We should watch our own gossiping and anger. We should model the kindness we want to see.', 247, 0), (493331, 'Allowing children to show their guilt, show their grief, show their anger, takes the sting out of the situation.', 29471, 0), (493332, 'I don''t think enough players channel the energy of the crowd. If it''s done properly, and you don''t let anger overwhelm and distract you, it''s like a shot of adrenaline in the arm, and it gets the crowd pumped up.', 63558, 0), (493333, 'As I got older and started moving up the ranking, the matches got more important, and my emotions ratcheted up. I guess I hid my real feelings behind the anger.', 63558, 0), (493334, 'The dog is often quick to resent a kick, be it from man or beast, but I have never known him to show anger at the door that slammed to and hit him. Probably, if the door held him by his tail or his limb, it would quickly receive the imprint of his teeth.', 1069, 0), (493335, 'Fair peace becomes men ferocious anger belongs to beasts. ', 782, 0), (493336, 'Like fragile ice anger passes away in time.', 782, 0), (493337, 'One of the interesting things about comedy is it''s tension release, and nothing creates tension faster than anger.', 1870, 0), (493338, 'When you create an economy where you subsidize corporate profits through a welfare program and food stamps in order to keep wages low in some perverse pursuit of ''competiveness,'' than you reap the fruits of the anger that you sow.', 67011, 0), (493339, 'I''m an angry person, angrier than most people would imagine, I get flashes of anger. What works for me is working out when it''s useful to use that anger.', 15994, 0), (493340, 'I''m too mature to be angry.', 23411, 0), (493341, 'Many are observing Ferguson and witnessing the anger, demonstrations, looting and vandalism and calling for quiet. But quiet isn''t enough. The absence of noise isn''t the presence of justice - and we must demand justice in Ferguson and the other ''Fergusons'' around America.', 23411, 0), (493342, 'I have been to anger management twice. After the first session the lady was like, ''Baby, you don''t seem that angry at all. You seem like a really nice guy.''', 67013, 0), (493343, 'Sometimes, you have to get angry to get things done.', 69896, 0), (493344, 'Democracies are slow to anger and hesitant to go to war: Voters don''t want to sacrifice their children for the glory of a selfish king.', 1821, 0), (493345, 'My father had a real short fuse. He had a tough life - had to support his mother and brother at a very young age when his dad''s farm collapsed. You could see his suffering, his terrible suffering, living a life that was disappointing and looking for another one. My father was full of terrifying anger.', 9118, 0), (493346, 'Unpleasant reading on the subject of anger tells us that there''s not really anything wrong with it. In limited amounts. It can even be a good thing. A pressure valve.', 12902, 0), (493347, 'I think we all have a lot of darkness in our bellies. As an actor, the challenge of tapping into that, reaching down into that sadness or anger, is very therapeutic.', 26931, 0), (493348, 'I started a youth center in Houston. The kids would come in and want to learn to box; they wanted to tear up the world, beat up the world. And I''d try to show them they didn''t need anger. They didn''t need all that killing instinct they''d read about. You can be a human being and pursue boxing as a sport.', 26132, 0), (493349, 'What people don''t realize about Donald Trump - and I don''t even know if Donald Trump realizes it - is that every tweet he unleashes against you... creates such a crescendo of anger.', 8452, 0), (493350, 'Anger is one of the sinews of the soul.', 1348, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493351, 'Lawyers are men who hire out their words and anger.', 2542, 0), (493352, 'He that would be angry and sin not, must not be angry with anything but sin.', 485, 0), (493353, 'Boxing was a way to express my anger. All of a sudden, I was expressing anger, and I was good at it. I was like a Jekyll and Hyde. Boxing helped me because I was fighting the anger out. I was knocking guys out.', 68906, 0), (493354, 'Boxing gave me a voice to express the anger I felt for where I came from.', 68906, 0), (493355, 'It''s usually a big kind of vent of frustration or anger or sadness that puts me in the right frame of mind to write. It''s such a cliche to say that artists write when they''re down, but it''s true for me. It''s a relief to get out what''s eating away at my heart or my soul or my head.', 16756, 0), (493356, 'All improv turns into anger. All comedy improv basically turns into anger, because that''s all people know how to do when they''re improvising. If you notice shows that are improvising are generally people yelling at each other.', 61610, 0), (493357, 'I think anger and laughter are very close to each other, when you think about it.', 61610, 0), (493358, 'Even in my comedies, I don''t take anger as a joke. I think anger and laughter are very close to each other, when you think about it. One of the things I like about a character: I always think it''s fascinating when a character can turn on a dime and go from one emotion to another. I like watching that.', 61610, 0), (493359, 'The difference between anger and deep remorse - remorse is much fatter. It''s a deeper feeling altogether. Anger is too easy an escape for my money.', 67836, 0), (493360, 'I''ve never felt that anger is a very powerful emotion.', 67836, 0), (493361, 'An angry people cannot create anything that is not imbued with anger.', 53514, 0), (493362, 'A theme that has always interested me is how women express anger, how women express violence. That is very much part of who women are, and it''s so unaddressed. A vast amount of literature deals with cycles of violence about men, antiheroes. Women lack that vocabulary.', 236, 0), (493363, 'Well, all comedy starts with anger. You get angry, and its never for a good reason, right? You know its not a good reason. And then you try and work it from there.', 2195, 0), (493364, 'Hizb ut-Tahrir spearheaded the radicalization of the 1990s and cultivated an atmosphere of anger.', 10487, 0), (493365, 'When daughters react with annoyance or even anger at the smallest, seemingly innocent remarks, mothers get the feeling that talking to their daughters can be like walking on eggshells: they have to watch every word.', 41330, 0), (493366, 'Conversations with sisters can spark extremes of anger or extremes of love. Everything said between sisters carries meaning not only from what was just said but from all the conversations that came before - and ''before'' can span a lifetime. The layers of meaning combine profound connection with equally profound competition.', 41330, 0), (493367, 'I find there''s this weird anger thing: Someone will approach me at the bar and say, ''Hey, can I buy you a drink?'' And I''ll say, ''No, I''m okay.'' And then all of a sudden, there''s this male anger flip, where they go, ''Oh, you know what? I wasn''t even gonna buy you a drink, ''cause you''re not even that cute anyway,'' and walk away.', 69341, 0), (493368, 'Experts say you should never hit your children in anger. When is a good time? When you''re feeling festive?', 18054, 0), (493369, 'The modern progressive movement believes that dissenting language is objectionable, which then removes the brakes between anger and violence.', 10679, 0), (493370, 'A lot of artists think they want anger. But a real, strong, bitter anger occupies the mind, leaving no room for creativity.', 18666, 0), (493371, 'Anger clearly has its proper place at work, which is neither wholly absent nor ever present. The manager who is an emotional blank is just as hard to work for as the volcanic boss, and both can do great harm by setting an unhelpful example for what kind of emotional expression is expected and accepted.', 67531, 0), (493372, 'The most powerful force in American politics is not anger, it''s nostalgia.', 2553, 0), (493373, 'If people think I''m angry, I don''t want to burst anybody''s bubble. I like sometimes for people to be afraid of me. But it''s not really anger; it''s discipline.', 66917, 0), (493374, 'Basically, it''s in your best mental interest to release your anger so you can see the world more clearly around you and seek better solutions for finding the happy, love-filled life you desire and deserve.', 5238, 0), (493375, 'Often, overeating is a way to punish yourself for the anger and resentment you''re feeling - either at yourself or someone else.', 5238, 0), (493376, 'If your partner is angry with you, recognize that his anger is a misdirected plea for love. Your partner''s simply upset because he feels something you said or did was a sign of not loving him enough.', 5238, 0), (493377, 'Anger in the black community towards Republicans is established and immutable.', 68438, 0), (493378, 'When our neighbor''s personality possesses harsh qualities, we show our love by not voluntarily provoking those qualities in any way. Past experience shows us what upsets a person, so in their presence we are careful not to do or say those things that cause anger. We are self-effacing.', 9130, 0), (493379, 'When anyone arouses my anger, I will immediately pray for them and regain my peace of soul.', 9130, 0), (493380, 'You look at 30 Seconds to Mars, and you don''t think, ''Ooh, I bet they''re angry.'' No one really does anger these days. I suppose it''s a turn-off.', 19787, 0), (493381, 'Staring prejudice in the face imposes a cruel discipline: to structure your anger, to achieve a certain dignity, an angry dignity.', 49869, 0), (493382, 'Anger is so constructive.', 57404, 0), (493383, 'I''ve been in government and politics my entire career, and while I try to keep a level head and a reasonable tone in my commentary, even I can lose my head sometimes and let anger bubble over and burst out. It feels gross, looks ugly, and leaves a lasting mark.', 61931, 0), (493384, 'It angers me to see armed defenders at the bottom of Lost Cause statues, adding a renewed threat of violence to icons that are themselves part of an ideology of violence and intimidation.', 14605, 0), (493385, 'You see all the movies where people say, ''Don''t fight out of anger''? They say that for a reason.', 71229, 0), (493386, 'For me, the interesting thing about anorexia is that you show your wound. There''s no hiding it. So my anger and sense of disappointment, all the stuff I was out of touch with, became this visible rebuke to my parents.', 2308, 0), (493387, 'Anger is a good motivator.', 11508, 0), (493388, 'When I interviewed John McCain in 2000 about whether he had taken medication for his anger, I remember thinking, ''Let''s see how this is going to work.''', 69135, 0), (493389, 'Anger is one of those emotions that doesn''t follow the letter of the law. It speaks before it thinks. It rears up on its hind legs and charges.', 9037, 0), (493390, 'When you''re not sure your anger is justified, the thing to do is ask yourself exactly where it''s coming from.', 9037, 0), (493391, 'What we Americans go through to pick a president is not only crazy and unnecessary but genuinely abusive. Hundreds of millions of dollars are spent in a craven, cynical effort to stir up hatred and anger on both sides.', 2829, 0), (493392, 'George wrote Taxman, and I played guitar on it. He wrote it in anger at finding out what the taxman did. He had never known before then what could happen to your money.', 67, 0), (493393, 'There''s a lot of anger in ''Queen of Denmark,'' and that''s me getting political.', 67046, 0), (493394, 'I have not one shred of anger in my heart against Netanyahu or his wife.', 67863, 0), (493395, 'I get angry at a principle, not a person.', 4137, 0), (493396, 'I have rage and anger issues. So I get mad about stuff in real life, and then I yell about it onstage, and luckily, something funny ends up coming out. What I''ll do is tape-record it, and it will end up coming out even funnier. And I add more punch lines.', 71307, 0), (493397, 'I don''t like anybody to be angry with me. I''d rather have friends.', 22887, 0), (493398, 'Shock, confusion, fear, anger, grief, and defiance. On Sept. 11, 2001, and for the three days following the worst terrorist attack on U.S. soil, President George W. Bush led with raw emotion that reflected the public''s whipsawing stages of acceptance.', 27482, 0), (493399, 'When I first started, my songs were the politics of anger. As I got older and hopefully wiser, I wanted to be part of the politics of answers.', 21674, 0), (493400, 'Whoever incites anger has a strong insurance against indifference.', 68382, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493401, 'I think I''m basically the same guy I always was. Maybe I''ve learned, through experience, to rein in some of the anger and temper they say redheads normally have.', 16011, 0), (493402, 'A lot of these guys come up and say, ''Man, you were my influence, the way you thrashed the drums.'' They don''t seem to understand I was thrashing in order to hear what I was playing. It was anger, not enjoyment - and painful.', 71036, 0), (493403, 'We do have our challenges. Some things don''t always work right in Washington, and the anger you see from the electorate, I think, is a reflection of what''s not working right.', 68270, 0), (493404, 'I was being very bad because I didn''t know how to express myself. Music gave me an outlet to express myself and channel that anger.', 73209, 0), (493405, 'Anger tears me up inside... My own... or anyone else''s.', 1377, 0), (493406, 'Our government is printing money, and it''s degrading the living standard of every person in America. It''s the cause of frustration, anger, and confusion.', 67055, 0), (493407, 'When the Left agitates over government policies, it''s considered righteous anger. When the Right - and much of the center - agitate, it''s painted as the rantings of the criminally and violently insane.', 68666, 0), (493408, 'My passion and energy get mistaken for anger.', 3625, 0), (493409, 'I drank for about 25 years getting over the loss of my father and I took the anger out on myself. I did a good job at beating myself up at sometimes. I don''t drink anymore but my alcoholic head occasionally says different. ''Nil By Mouth'' was a love letter to my father because I needed to resolve some issues in order to be able to forgive him.', 3625, 0), (493410, 'I asked a shrink: ''Everything is so great. Why am I still so angry?'' He said, ''Anger doesn''t go away.'' I always thought it was kind of a good engine.', 23139, 0), (493411, 'The Clash had a unique, special relationship with Scotland. Perhaps it was something to do with the energy, anger and beauty in their music. In Scotland at that time, there was a lot of to be angry about. And a great need of some energy and beauty.', 27413, 0), (493412, 'I think I have more humour in me than anger. But those two things are great bed-fellows, performance-wise.', 56664, 0), (493413, 'I accrued anger from people''s low opinion of me and my work, and for the work I might be capable of.', 12392, 0), (493414, 'I don''t think anybody should ever touch anybody in anger, ever.', 11490, 0), (493415, 'I could feel my moral compass as a soldier, in danger of - I could feel the squeeze, the pressure of frustration and anger and fear combining on me... I felt the danger; I felt the squeeze of it.', 3159, 0), (493416, 'Democracy isn''t solely about polite conversations in parliaments. It needs to be continually refreshed with raw passions, anger and ideals.', 70907, 0), (493417, 'One effect of an individualistic culture that''s poor at instilling mutual respect is that people jump more quickly to anger or violence.', 70907, 0), (493418, 'When terrorism strikes, divisive anger is a natural response.', 5980, 0), (493419, 'If you feel like there is going to be an emotional reaction that won''t be helpful to resolve the situation, anger or other things, disarm the situation in some way, and you can use different techniques to do that.', 71245, 0), (493420, 'My whole life, people have been saying, Why are you so angry?', 15776, 0), (493421, 'I almost failed out of high school. I nearly gave in to the deep anger and resentment harbored by everyone around me... Whatever talents I have, I almost squandered until a handful of loving people rescued me.', 9371, 0), (493422, 'Yeah, to me, acting is very therapeutic. I get out a lot of anger and frustration.', 70263, 0), (493423, 'I want roles without anger and feistiness. I want to show weakness and sadness, some love, some happiness.', 67063, 0), (493424, 'I''m sure it''s one of the most frustrating aspects of human experience for all of us, that when we tell someone who''s hurt us that they''ve hurt us, they tend to react with anger because they feel guilty, and we know we also get angry when we feel guilty.', 68282, 0), (493425, 'An angry man is again angry with himself when he returns to reason.', 2904, 0), (493426, 'The bare recollection of anger kindles anger.', 2904, 0), (493427, 'I have some anger issues.', 33509, 0), (493428, 'A very powerful mechanism to get elected is to play on anger and pick those wedge issues.', 70522, 0), (493429, 'I had a lot of anger inside me and that came out at times that were not particularly advantageous to me career-wise.', 70061, 0), (493430, 'Solitude is the place where we can connect with profound bonds that are deeper than the emergency bonds of fear and anger.', 19097, 0), (493431, 'Of course we need to show we are a genuine alternative to an unpopular, Conservative-led government. But we need to set ourselves a higher standard than a party offering anger like UKIP.', 69492, 0), (493432, 'The upside to anger? Getting it out of your system. You got to express your anger. Then you have room for more positive things. If I hold something in a long time, and then I speak it, it''s amazing how the light shines so much brighter.', 1356, 0), (493433, 'I''ve been trying to learn how to not be so conflicted about things like my own anger. I''ve always had a place in my music for my anger as a way of compensating for not having a mechanism to express it in my everyday life. So I''ve been trying to be more true to myself, and that helps me to chill out a little bit. But politically, uh-uh. No.', 1251, 0), (493434, 'Men make angry music and it''s called rock-and-roll women include anger in their vocabulary and suddenly they''re angry and militant. ', 1251, 0), (493435, 'I think I deal with my anger toward my relationship or about my relationship or about my friendships or my family - I deal with it on stage in a passive-aggressive way, and that can be very harmful if it gets back to them, which it always does.', 68458, 0), (493436, 'I think it''s too easy to recount your unhappy memories when you write about yourself. You bask in your own innocence. You revere your grief. You arrange your angers at their most becoming angles.', 68863, 0), (493437, 'I have now been married to my third husband for more than 20 years. But when you''ve had children with someone you''re divorced from, divorce defines everything; it''s the lurking fact, a slice of anger in the pie of your brain.', 301, 0), (493438, 'One good thing I''d like to say about divorce is that it sometimes makes it possible for you to be a much better wife to your next husband because you have a place for your anger - it''s not directed at the person you''re currently with.', 301, 0), (493439, 'The biggest aggravation in the Arab world, the biggest reason for their anger toward us and the creation of those suicide terrorists, is Israel and the difficulty with the Palestinian issue.', 8855, 0), (493440, 'I am just sorry my own mother had to live under that regime for most of her life. I was lucky. I got out and, 14 years later, Czechoslovakia became a free country. So I feel anger, even fury, at this bloody system that ruined so many people''s lives for no reason whatsoever.', 34262, 0), (493441, 'How do you redefine love when your idea of love is something that''s so violent? When your idea of passion is anger, how do you fix that?', 694, 0), (493442, 'We don''t get the greatest tools to deal with anger. It''s like, ''Hey, count to 10.'' When someone really upsets me, how do I respond? I don''t usually start counting to 10 and breathing deeply.', 68702, 0), (493443, 'Sometimes you just need to raise your voice. And sometimes a little anger is necessary, to be honest.', 68463, 0), (493444, 'The great thing about celebrity culture is that they can''t seem to stop themselves from displaying their ridiculous behaviour. I feel it''s my job as a serious investigative journalist to witness all kinds of behaviour and then report back to the audience through the prism of my own anger and bitterness.', 2356, 0), (493445, 'Anger has a way of seeping into every other emotion and planting itself in there.', 21158, 0), (493446, 'There''s a certain time that when somebody asks you a question, you answer them. I don''t think I said anything with venom. If you can express yourself without anger and make it as palatable as you can, that''s what you do.', 65245, 0), (493447, 'I do like to write nasty songs. It''s a useful weapon to have, and it''s cathartic as well, because I create art out of anger, something positive out of something negative.', 68955, 0), (493448, 'A lot of people think they should be happy all the time. But the writer understands you need both. You need the whole piano: the richness of the whole human experience. Depression, suffering and anger are all part of being human.', 524, 0), (493449, 'When you learn that a truth is a lie, anger follows.', 64763, 0), (493450, 'At the time, 1980, people regarded actresses involved with production with a certain amount of fear, resentment and anger.', 18672, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493451, 'What the media misses is the amount of anger that''s out there. Trump didn''t create that.', 69762, 0), (493452, 'I think that Scottish people, like Canadians, are often misunderstood and what I like about my Scottish friends and relatives is how quickly it can go from love to anger. It''s a great dynamic.', 68365, 0), (493453, 'September 11 was a wake-up call to me. I don''t want to contribute to the hate in any shape or form. I now regret in the past being silent about what I have heard in the Islamic discourse and being part of that with my own anger.', 4723, 0), (493454, 'Being an activist is about getting things done. It''s not about standing around shaking your fist in anger.', 67488, 0), (493455, 'And I think there''s something about conservatives frankly - and the Left, when it comes to their channels of persuasion, are unpersuasive. They are, most of them are hate-filled, obscenity-clogged rants of anger and hatred.', 69276, 0), (493456, 'It really shocked me just to hear of the fans'' response to ''St. Anger'' not having guitar solos.', 69938, 0), (493457, 'Metallica is like the phoenix rising from the ashes. We set everything on fire, and this is what has risen from it - ''St. Anger'' being the fire and ''Death Magnetic'' being the phoenix.', 69938, 0), (493458, 'People who think that Sylvia Plath was a poor, sensitive poet are not getting that she had great amounts of ambition and anger that moved her along, or she wouldn''t have been able to fight against that depression to produce such an incredible body of work by the age of thirty.', 539, 0), (493459, 'In high school I dated a white woman. She would come to visit me on the rez. And her dad, who was very racist, didn''t like that at all. And he told her one time, ''You shouldn''t go on the rez if you''re white because Indians have a lot of anger in their heart.''', 360, 0), (493460, 'My biggest influence is rap. It spoke to me, probably because of my upbringing in Christiania. You listen to ''The Chronic'' and you can hear that anger and frustration.', 73213, 0), (493461, 'When you get frisked by the police at the age of 10, and they empty your schoolbag out in the street and kick your books around and calling you names because of where you live, you just get an anger towards everyone who is outside of your neighborhood.', 73213, 0), (493462, 'The anger and the creativity are so closely intertwined with me, and there''s plenty of anger left.', 3396, 0), (493463, 'When I played a club in Salt Lake City, I complained to the crowd about the low turnout. It''s always good to berate the people who paid to see you because you''re upset about the people who didn''t show up. It''s called misplaced anger, and without it, I wouldn''t have an act.', 68469, 0), (493464, 'Every now and then, when I think about it, I think, ''What would I even talk about onstage?'' It''s never been, ''I wonder if I''m funny. I wonder if I can come up with jokes.'' It''s more, ''What would it be like without the leather suit and the anger?''', 71878, 0), (493465, 'Perhaps it should be obvious: Adultery is a social threat that arouses raw anger and fear, which the bellicose then need to discharge rather than merely feel, traditionally on the philandering wife or the female home-wrecker.', 9634, 0), (493466, 'I use the music to vent, and a lot of the stuff that I am writing about or was writing about contained a lot of anger and anxiety, stress and depression, so that''s how the album came out so dark.', 69363, 0), (493467, 'The Internet is a cauldron of anger every day, every year, election year or not, with unemployment at 10 percent or at two percent. It isn''t exactly a good index of what''s happening.', 45527, 0), (493468, 'Fear, separation, hate and anger come from the wrong view that you and the Earth are two separate entities, the Earth is only the environment. You are in the centre, and you want to do something for the Earth in order for you to survive.', 69092, 0), (493469, 'I don''t display emotions. I have every feeling that everyone else has, but I''ve developed ways to suppress them. Anger is one of my most comfortable feelings.', 68146, 0), (493470, 'Sometimes, you have to make the choice to forgive 10 times a day when you have these pockets of anger come up. That''s a lot of work, but to me it''s worthwhile.', 16246, 0), (493471, 'I''ve become a lot more tolerant; I think before I talk. I can take a lot now. I don''t get as angry as I used to. Whenever I do, I channel my anger into my work.', 47352, 0), (493472, 'He took over anger to intimidate subordinates, and in time anger took over him.', 61, 0), (493473, 'Caregiving requires the intention of love, caretaking requires the intention of fear. Not acting in anger when you are angry requires the intention of love.', 21209, 0), (493474, 'I have to say that anger is the blanket that comes around me, and that blunts and blurs my sense of proportion.', 22792, 0), (493475, 'People are unjust to anger - it can be enlivening and a lot of fun.', 398, 0), (493476, 'I am a danger to myself if I get angry.', 10057, 0), (493477, 'Before I came out, I had a lot of anger. For years people would ask, ''How are you doing?'' and I''d say, ''Good, fine.'' It''s show business, and that''s what you have to show.', 67432, 0), (493478, 'All through life I''ve harbored anger rather than expressed it at the moment.', 62315, 0), (493479, 'I understand Tea Partyers'' anger with the system, but they are in way over their heads and often racially motivated, and I can''t be part of that.', 51830, 0), (493480, 'Do not follow vain desires; for verily he who prospers is preserved from lust, greed and anger.', 70609, 0), (493481, 'We need to learn how to organize, not just to let our anger explode. We need to have organization for the long run, not for one issue, not for one murder, but for everything coming to us in the next 20, 30 years.', 68963, 0), (493482, 'Yes, an individual could be electronically stimulated to fear, anger, or euphoria from a distance. However, the procedure is complicated, not always accurate, and far too tedious and expensive as a method for taking over control of the world.', 62855, 0), (493483, 'The best therapists can do with sadness, anger, and anxiety is to help patients live in the more comfortable part of their set range.', 67434, 0), (493484, 'Eventually, I moved from a place of anger toward the Jews of Israel toward a place of embrace.', 71509, 0), (493485, 'Many of us who have cars have felt some form of extreme anger at other drivers because we feel they have put us in harm''s way. We might even envision ramming their cars or cutting them off in return, but do we actually do it? No, because the overwhelming majority of us never want to take another human life.', 72821, 0), (493486, 'I guess I probably make violent films partly because I can''t express my anger in my real life very well.', 73774, 0), (493487, 'So I''m not worried about the emotions I carry with me, because I''m happy that I have them; I think it''s good for the work I do. The emotions that are not healthy are the ones you hold inside, like anger.', 55180, 0), (493488, 'It''s that evil twin part of me that always comes out at the absolute wrong political moment, like a demon possessing my soul; it exhibits itself as an arrogance or disdain or obnoxiousness or meanness or anger or pettiness - all traits that are lethal in politics.', 67884, 0), (493489, 'Whether one agrees or disagrees with the tactics of the Occupy Wall Street movement, it''s easy to understand the inspiration for its anger as well as its impatience.', 75005, 0), (493490, 'I believe anger is a wasted emotion, and I don''t like to waste emotions.', 73042, 0), (493491, 'Contempt is the only asymmetrical expression in the muscular facial system: Disgust, fear, happiness, surprise and anger typically express themselves symmetrically. Contempt is marked by one lip corner pulled up and in a dismissive sneer.', 73298, 0), (493492, 'When we can lay down our fear and anger and choose responses other than aggression, we create the conditions for bringing out the best in us humans.', 29442, 0), (493493, 'My humour has always come from anger, but I have to make sure I don''t just get angry and jump on a soapbox.', 2257, 0), (493494, 'Anger is not an accepted thing for women. And, you know, I do get angry. I feel it''s a very honest emotion.', 72920, 0), (493495, 'On banks, I make no apology for attacking spivs and gamblers who did more harm to the British economy than Bob Crow could achieve in his wildest Trotskyite fantasies, while paying themselves outrageous bonuses underwritten by the taxpayer. There is much public anger about banks and it is well deserved.', 66807, 0), (493496, 'Something my mum taught me years and years and years ago, is life''s just too short to carry around a great bucket-load of anger and resentment and bitterness and hatreds and all that sort of stuff.', 67684, 0), (493497, 'Imagine how much capital a country like Argentina might attract - if instead of defaulting seriatim and affecting a pose of anger toward creditors, it borrowed responsibly and honored its obligations.', 67549, 0), (493498, 'I grew up looking at my father as to how to behave. In watching him I grasped so many things. His own temperament was of a calm person. He was very composed and I never saw anger in him. To me, that was fascinating.', 5213, 0), (493499, 'Once in a while, I still witness occasionally sexist behavior and comments from men (which experience has taught me you should always deflect with humour rather than anger). Old habits die hard, after all, and it''s unrealistic to expect dinosaurs to fall silent overnight.', 71512, 0), (493500, 'As the plane got closer to Miami, I had this terrible feeling he was dying. Maybe he was telling me that he was going. I felt anger, panic, despair and helplessness.', 68002, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493501, 'Quite a lot of our contemporary culture is actually shot through with a resentment of limits and the passage of time, anger at what we can''t do, fear or even disgust at growing old.', 9221, 0), (493502, 'I wasn''t a very academic kid, and music was the way for all that feeling and angst and sex and love and anger to be channelled.', 70790, 0), (493503, 'Dance music cannot compete with a really great rock n'' roll song. There ain''t no DJ that''s gonna play something that can take ''Mr Brightside'' or ''Don''t Look Back In Anger.''', 75194, 0), (493504, 'From my anger, frustration, and hurt, I wrote the short story that would later become ''The Hate U Give.''', 14707, 0), (493505, 'I feel like we sometimes let our emotions and anger get in the way.', 74383, 0), (493506, 'I resisted writing a book for a long time because I didn''t want to invade anyone else''s privacy or hurt anyone or anger anyone.', 68855, 0), (493507, 'In one sense, every character you create will be yourself. You''ve never murdered, but your murderer''s rage will be drawn from memories of your own extreme anger. Your love scenes will contain hints of your own past kisses and sweet moments.', 11182, 0), (493508, 'People have said I''m the candidate of anger. Well, we have a right to be angry. We lost 3 million jobs. We lost our place as the moral leader of the world.', 17529, 0), (493509, 'I had lived with my mother in anger and love - I suppose most daughters do - but my children only knew her in one way: As the lady who thought they were smarter than Albert Einstein. As the lady who thought they wrote better than William Shakespeare. As the lady who thought every picture they drew was a Rembrandt.', 29209, 0), (493510, 'But one of the hardest things for me to do was to access anger. I could do it on stage. But when I did it on film it was hard for me. That probably has to do with the intimacy of film. And my own personal issues with expressing anger. So I had to learn how to do that.', 67842, 0), (493511, 'There''s no anger ever in a spiritual. There''s always the dream of a hope of a better day coming. That God understands the troubles that I''m experiencing.', 65864, 0), (493512, 'I had a lot of anger because I wasn''t happy with the way I had been raised.', 2110, 0), (493513, 'Green Arrow has gone through so many changes; he''s been right-wing, he''s been left-wing, he''s been rich, he''s been poor, he''s been a social justice guy, then when I got him, he was a rich playboy guy. So it was a lot harder to get into a character that has so many personas in the past, and I just looked at his anger.', 75911, 0), (493514, 'Tel Aviv is buzzing with so much life, you could bottle it and sell it as honey, and even Jerusalem has a certain fizz. But if you want to see anger, go to Sheikh Jarrah in East Jerusalem on a Friday afternoon.', 69485, 0), (493515, 'Psychologists, for reasons of clinical necessity or vagaries of temperament, have chosen to dissect and catalog the morbid emotions - depression, anger, anxiety - and to leave largely unexamined the more vital, positive ones.', 1631, 0), (493516, 'If you''re writing about angry people, you use the language of anger. If you''re writing about desperate people, you use the language of desperation.', 3265, 0), (493517, 'I think anger is a normal response to something horrible that someone has done, another human being has done, and to rob people of life, and that''s actually healthy to have, to feel that. At some point you have to figure out, ''How do I let that go?''', 19140, 0), (493518, 'I''ve written for the last 15 years on TV shows, but now I''m doing the new Charlie Sheen program, ''Anger Management.''', 70287, 0), (493519, 'Human anger does not produce the righteousness that God desires.', 14894, 0), (493520, 'The anger of lovers renews their love.', 21159, 0), (493521, 'He that will be angry for anything will be angry for nothing.', 4812, 0), (493522, 'It doesn''t pay to say too much when you are mad enough to choke. For the word that stings the deepest is the word that is never spoke, Let the other fellow wrangle till the storm has blown away, then he''ll do a heap of thinking about the things you didn''t say.', 1952, 0), (493523, 'God''s love-eye does not see essentially into the wicked rebellious apostate soul; neither also into the devil, but his anger-eye sees thereinto; that is, God, according to the property of the anger or fire of wrath, sees in the devil, and in the false soul.', 5825, 0), (493524, 'Anger, and the self-righteousness that is both the cause and consequence of anger, tends to be easier on the psyche than personal responsibility.', 3119, 0), (493525, 'We are children of the eternity: But this world is an out-birth out of the eternal and its palpability taketh its original in the anger the eternal nature is its root. ', 5825, 0), (493526, 'I''m not as angry as I used to be. But I can get in touch with that anger pretty quickly if I feel my space is being invaded or somebody is not treating me with the respect that I think I want.', 73054, 0), (493527, 'When you feel bad, find a person to talk to and cry with, to tell of your anger and other helpless feelings.', 625, 0), (493528, 'I think there is a big difference between expressing the pain and anger that many African Americans and other people of color may feel versus language that I think now crosses the line and goes into hate.', 71064, 0), (493529, 'All anger is not sinful, because some degree of it, and on some occasions, is inevitable. But it becomes sinful and contradicts the rule of Scripture when it is conceived upon slight and inadequate provocation, and when it continues long.', 63304, 0), (493530, 'I was a confused young girl with so much tragedy. Sometimes when you''re going through stuff, the last person you''re thinking exists is God. I mean, it was my confusion, the anger that was in my heart, all that drama. But thank God I know God now, okay?', 67679, 0), (493531, 'I''m a bit of an expert on anger, having suffered from it all through my youth, when I was both brunt and font. It''s certainly the most miserable state to be in but it''s also tremendously gratifying, really - rage feels justified.', 15474, 0), (493532, 'Ours is a country where anything can be accomplished if enough people get angry... because, in America, we act on our collective anger.', 10851, 0), (493533, 'I think anger is a good thing.', 74242, 0), (493534, 'Like every art form, there are jealousies and angers and competitiveness in magic. But there''s camaraderie among magicians, whether you perform it for a living or you''re an enthusiast.', 75912, 0), (493535, 'For me music is a vehicle to bring our pain to the surface, getting it back to that humble and tender spot where, with luck, it can lose its anger and become compassion again.', 72299, 0), (493536, 'On stage, I find anger at the unfairness of the world easily.', 68054, 0), (493537, 'A dirty player is somebody who ultimately is trying to hurt somebody. There''s a huge difference. There''s no gray in that. Like, you have no conscience, no nothing, no guilt. I don''t have that mean streak in me. I don''t play angry. It''s not anger.', 75913, 0), (493538, 'It''s very shocking, I think, for people caring for the dying to realise how unsaintly they feel, how much anger is mixed up with their grief. In fact, often I think the anger that they feel is a form of grief; it''s a kind of raging against what''s happening.', 45504, 0), (493539, 'I''d be lying if I said I wasn''t angry some days. But I really have worked hard to put a lot of the anger and disappointment in the past.', 68534, 0), (493540, 'I suppose there''s an anger in all of us. Some hidden rage that you keep at bay.', 71083, 0), (493541, 'Nobody can take what I love away from me. I would like to believe that love is the only energy I''ve ever used as a writer. I''ve never written out of anger, although anger has informed love.', 9896, 0), (493542, 'I''ve learned that football sometimes was an outlet. It was a way for me to release anger, release frustration.', 68118, 0), (493543, 'Of the seven deadly sins, anger has long been the one with the best box of costumes. When the guy in the next car rages at you, he''s dangerous. When you rage at him, you''re just. We can usually recognize the results of anger, especially in others, as destructive and evil.', 9178, 0), (493544, 'I''m not sure why there''s this anger in the youth, but we need to talk about it. Kids need to get help if they need help, and bullies need to be helped as well.', 75914, 0), (493545, 'I have a lot of anger about my childhood - being hard of hearing and my relationship with my father.', 29646, 0), (493546, 'My tastes lean toward the more negative, angry and eclectic.', 75915, 0), (493547, 'I think photographers are too polite. There is not enough anger in photography it''s pretty much trivialized. ', 19769, 0), (493548, 'I''ve spent a lot of time and money trying to keep my anger in control.', 71764, 0), (493549, 'If there are a couple of adjectives people use to describe me, anger is usually in there. I''ve never taken that as criticism. It''s the way I naturally communicate. But I''m not faux-angry, like Lewis Black, or angry like a gun-toting crazy person. I''m just angry in a mild way - it''s not like I''m going to do anything about it.', 13111, 0), (493550, 'Since the time of Richard Nixon, there has been a strange lack of will in the media to identify the real cause for Americans'' anger at politicians who fall, publicly and spectacularly.', 73530, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493551, 'I would say that I definitely became much more religious. They say there are no atheists in foxholes, and this stroke put me into a very deep foxhole. Yet that feeling of faith sustained me, so I have no feelings of anger or regret.', 72152, 0), (493552, 'Never go to bed angry, stay up and fight.', 14081, 0), (493553, 'Americans are slow to anger, but once they do get angry, they are impossible to stop.', 72153, 0), (493554, 'I guess because I had such a horrible life growing up, going from place to place not knowing what I was gonna do and ending up being homeless, there was a lot of pain and a lot of anger that was coming out through my guitar playing.', 8226, 0), (493555, 'There aren''t very many good models of feminine rage - and the ones that we remember are ones where women take that anger internally and implode themselves in a real way, like Anna Karenina or Emma Bovary.', 9575, 0), (493556, 'But on second thought, after I decreed the state of emergency, I came to the conclusion that that was impossible to achieve without bloodshed because the street protesters were full of anger and nearly out of control. This is why I thought we needed to find another way out.', 73069, 0), (493557, 'I''m not a screamer. I''m confrontational, but I don''t think that translates into anger.', 3180, 0), (493558, 'I''ve got rid of a lot of cynicism and anger. I feel positive about my development, and I just want to carry on making music and building myself as a person.', 75916, 0), (493559, 'I''m generally quite an angry person, and I like to channel my anger toward something creative.', 68307, 0), (493560, 'Anger is never without an argument, but seldom with a good one.', 67404, 0), (493561, 'There''s simply anger over the accountability that Yelp brings and also this feeling of powerlessness because so much power is now being put in the hands of the consumer. But the important thing that gets lost with some of these business owners who are very upset with us is it''s the whole picture that counts.', 75263, 0), (493562, 'Dying peacefully means to avoid any immediate cause for anger, fear, or strong desire.', 69441, 0), (493563, 'A certain amount of anger doesn''t make us less empathetic, less humane, less loving. It just makes us real.', 74010, 0), (493564, 'Everybody kind of perceives me as being angry. It''s not anger, it''s motivation.', 72819, 0), (493565, 'I was able to do To Sleep with Anger, a very powerful film about African Americans, their spirituality, and the things that happened within a small community and a family.', 67506, 0), (493566, 'After my second-to-last record, ''The Greatest'', I had gone on tour for a while, and I didn''t play an instrument for about five years. And I got kind of - it''s not self-esteem or whatever, or anger toward myself - but disappointed in myself that I hadn''t been challenging myself to learn musically.', 75917, 0), (493567, 'A man can submit today in order to resist tomorrow. My submission had been such. And because I had not been free to show my real feeling, to voice my true thoughts, my submission had bred bitterness and anger. And there were nearly ten million others who had submitted with equal anger and bitterness.', 24318, 0), (493568, 'There never was a social change in America without angry people at the heart.', 13961, 0), (493569, 'I guess lyrically they''re similar because they''re talking about escaping the kind of misery that likes company. ''The Last One Alive,'' for me, is very simple. It''s just about alienation, really, that causes anger.', 71705, 0), (493570, 'To rule one''s anger is well to prevent it is better. ', 9316, 0), (493571, 'The more anger towards the past you carry in your heart, the less capable you are of loving in the present.', 28913, 0), (493572, 'I think I would cope like anyone copes with any tragedy. I''m sure I would be very upset for a while and then there would come a point where I would either have to stay in this place of darkness and anger, or I''d have to accept that it happened.', 72977, 0), (493573, 'Acting in anger and hatred throughout my life, I frequently precipitated what I feared most, the loss of friendships and the need to rely upon the very people I''d abused.', 75918, 0), (493574, 'Unless and until Barack Obama addresses the full depth of Americans'' anger with his full arsenal of policy smarts and political gifts, his presidency and, worse, our economy will be paralyzed.', 60510, 0), (493575, 'If anger proceeds from a great cause, it turns to fury; if from a small cause, it is peevishness; and so is always either terrible or ridiculous.', 3943, 0), (493576, 'I feel playful aggression is important for children because they have to deal with all kinds of anger and aggression in their lives.', 31331, 0), (493577, 'Anger is a transient hatred or at least very like it. ', 63015, 0), (493578, 'Always write angry letters to your enemies. Never mail them.', 70103, 0), (493579, 'I did not think that I was angry, but clearly anger was reflected in my writing. I did not think that I had been affected emotionally, but it was clear from my writing that I was still very emotional about the trial some six months after it ended.', 75919, 0), (493580, 'The Anger Management Tour was another beautiful thing. I loved that tour.', 75920, 0), (493581, 'What if you threw a protest and no one showed up? The lack of angst and anger and emotion is a big positive.', 73927, 0), (493582, 'I have moments of darkness, of anger, and moments of rage. They do creep up at the most inopportune times. Not to recognize that in my music would give people a sense of sainthood that I don''t necessarily have or even want to have.', 75921, 0), (493583, 'He best keeps from anger who remembers that God is always looking upon him.', 14130, 0), (493584, 'There''s definitely ways to get your anger out and not have to yell and kick and scream and fight people. That''s not my jam. That''s never how I''ve been.', 68587, 0), (493585, 'For all my success with the Ramones, I carried around fury and intensity during my career. I had an image, and that image was anger. I was the one who was always scowling, downcast. I tried to make sure I looked like that when I was getting my picture taken.', 15744, 0), (493586, 'I''m not angry, I''m not an angry person, but I do sometimes like playing with the perception of anger, as in pretending that I''m more angry than I actually am, and sometimes it works quite well.', 70107, 0), (493587, 'I do think anger is so difficult for women. Girls think it undermines their femininity it''s not very ladylike. ', 11906, 0), (493588, 'The further away we got from 9/11, the more I wanted to find some way to recover. I wanted to talk about the more anonymous corners of the city, because I think it''s very important that not all of that anger was turned to revenge.', 3367, 0), (493589, 'Being told about the effects of climate change is an appeal to our reason and to our desire to bring about change. But to see that Africans are the hardest hit by climate change, even though they generate almost no greenhouse gas, is a glaring injustice, which also triggers anger and outrage over those who seek to ignore it.', 73571, 0), (493590, 'I think what I learned in research is that as Americans, we''re very distrustful of anger. We''re not sure if we should repress it. The idea that anger is supposed to be controlled is American, and we try to keep it out of our homes.', 11906, 0), (493591, 'We are taught to believe it''s bad to be angry, or at least it''s not good. That''s not the case all throughout the world. People are more open and not embarrassed about it. For instance in Paris, people believe Americans have a really unhealthy relation with anger. They think it''s essential to get angry.', 11906, 0), (493592, 'I think, for one, we have to really accept that anger is a normal human emotion that can be a positive force for change.', 11906, 0), (493593, 'There is a real sense of anger among many people who are married that the government, any government, thinks it has the ability to change the definition of an institution like marriage.', 69548, 0), (493594, 'I''m not like most comedians. I don''t deal with just heckles - I''m also dealing with threats and anger. Here I am, a brown person on stage being quite blunt. I talk about white privilege; I talk about U.S. imperialistic practices; I talk about colonialism. I''m not saying things that are easy for people to laugh at.', 75922, 0), (493595, 'Bosnia is under my skin. It''s the place you cannot leave behind. I was obsessed by the nightmare of it all; there was this sense of guilt, and an anger that has become something much deeper over these last years.', 68875, 0), (493596, 'It''s true - my mother kicked me out the house at 14. I had to go live with my sister. I had some problems. I was very rebellious as a kid. I don''t even know why or where it came from, but I had a lot of anger. Me and my mom clashed a lot because she didn''t tolerate that, as she shouldn''t from a 14-year-old.', 69556, 0), (493597, 'I do play football no-holds-barred. Any edge I can get, I''ll take. I''d grab a face mask only in a fit of anger. Uncontrolled anger is damn near insane.', 67203, 0), (493598, 'I''ve seen my mother struggling, everything that she did to raise me and my brothers and my sisters, and I know the anger that she went through.', 70498, 0), (493599, 'I''ve purged myself of bitterness and anger and remained open to love.', 75923, 0), (493600, 'I was never jailed. The fact is that I was arrested, but I went into a diversion programme, and by that time I''d already begun working in what was called anger management. It was a painful and awful moment.', 72727, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493601, 'I''ve done a lot of dramedies in my career. You know, I started as a standup comic, and then the movies that I was doing, like ''Up Side of Anger'' were kind of like - they''re hard. They''re hard to sell; they''re hard to get made, you know.', 74532, 0), (493602, 'I literally used to stare at my face in the mirror with hate and anger. I''d focus on those gigantic zits and just wail about what a monster I was, how I would never have a career because of my gross skin. I couldn''t pass a mirror with out thinking about how hideous my skin was and how I wished I was someone else, someone with perfect skin.', 75924, 0), (493603, 'I share the anger, but, ultimately, to govern this country, it takes more than anger. It takes experience. It takes positions that reflect the best values of the American people.', 67938, 0), (493604, 'My character had been in the chair for seven years. He had gone through his anger, depression, drug and alcohol abuse. He had gone through everything, now he was up, he was happy, he was filled with his dream.', 75925, 0), (493605, 'It''s a very difficult thing for people to accept, seeing women act out anger on the screen. We''re more accustomed to seeing men expressing rage and women crying.', 75926, 0), (493606, 'If either player abandon the game by quitting the table in anger, or in an otherwise offensive manner; or by momentarily resigning the game; or refuses to abide by the decision of the Umpire, the game must be scored against him.', 75927, 0), (493607, 'Fear usually looks like anger.', 10493, 0), (493608, 'Our task, of course, is to transmute the anger that is affliction into the anger that is determination to bring about change. I think, in fact, that one could give that as a definition of revolution.', 49452, 0), (493609, 'The thing that started the peace movement in Ireland was anger - my anger. It wasn''t anger it was fury. ', 75651, 0), (493610, 'Anger does not solve problems - anger only makes things worse. I go by the old saying, ''Don''t make important decisions when you''re angry.''', 68223, 0), (493611, 'Anger''s not a good emotion.', 68766, 0), (493612, 'Many churches are measuring the wrong things. We measure things like attendance and giving, but we should be looking at more fundamental things like anger, contempt, honesty, and the degree to which people are under the thumb of their lusts. Those things can be counted, but not as easily as offerings.', 4361, 0), (493613, 'It is good to forget one''s anger against one''s wrongdoer, whoever he may be, for countless number of evils will quickly grow from this anger.', 4911, 0), (493614, 'I think the only time I show my emotions and anger is on the cricket field; otherwise, I''ve mellowed down. And with age, I think, with age you always end up mellowing down.', 73746, 0), (493615, 'And we know there has been horrendous loss of life and suffering and we know that there is anger. Anyone who came anywhere near the general election in constituencies with a substantial Muslim population knows that.', 68793, 0), (493616, 'I vent my anger in the gym, and it calms me down.', 75928, 0), (493617, 'I''m fascinated by rap and by hip-hop. I think there''s a lot of poetry in it. There''s a lot of anger, a lot of social energy in it. And I think you''d better listen to it pretty carefully, ''cause it''s important.', 16042, 0), (493618, 'If you''re an actor, and you''re selfish and not strong, it''s difficult to maintain a good personal life or a solid career, and I was selfish and had a lot of anger that went way back.', 75929, 0), (493619, 'My heart has been heavy and I have deliberated within my own conscience, knowing that my decision should not come out of my initial emotion of anger toward the President for such reckless behavior, but should be based on the facts.', 67784, 0), (493620, 'I also had to work through the violation of my date rape, my unhealthy relationships with men, my anger toward the people involved in the scandal, and those who exploited me afterwards.', 70469, 0), (493621, 'I like people and get along, and I''m afraid to express my anger and my rage.', 75930, 0), (493622, 'The greatest players use anger as fuel. Michael Jordan played every night with something like road rage.', 13883, 0), (493623, 'It''s something that black men still go through to this day, which is women clutching their purses, hitting the lock button on store, or just basic attitudes. And even as a U.S. congressman, as a black man, it is very, very frustrating, and you build up an internal anger about it that you can''t act on.', 71375, 0), (493624, 'I was shocked at the anger toward me.', 74618, 0), (493625, 'I know of no more disagreeable situation than to be left feeling generally angry without anybody in particular to be angry at.', 47554, 0), (493626, 'It''s interesting when you''re in your thirties and you''re not the same pretty boy that you were when you were 21. I think people''s anger at themselves getting older is projected on to you because you become a symbol of that.', 75931, 0), (493627, 'I had a job when I was 15 working at a supermarket, and I knocked over a stack of plastic coffee cups. In my anger, I threw one at a concrete wall, and it rebounded back into my head and cut my head open. Stupidest way to get a scar, but it''s one that I have.', 70547, 0), (493628, 'Another night, I dreamed I saw my father sweeping out the barn floor clean, and would not suffer the wheat to be brought in the barn. He appeared to me to be in anger.', 75932, 0), (493629, 'We are not actually in charge of life, yet behave as if we are the masters of our own destiny. The realization of this fact is quite a hard one. The ridiculousness of our pomposity and presumption can only result in anger or humor.', 69580, 0), (493630, 'In between shooting for ''Awake,'' I was attempting to have my own pilot season. The audition for ''Anger Management'' actually came during a week that I was already testing for a couple other shows and we weren''t really letting any other shows into the mix.', 73618, 0), (493631, 'On ''Awake,'' we would take a couple hours per scene. Whereas on ''Anger Management,'' we can take maybe 10 minutes on a scene if we''re lucky.', 73618, 0), (493632, 'I get really angry when I get hungry. If you don''t feed me, I won''t talk to you. That''s when my anger issues come out.', 73618, 0), (493633, 'I feel like everything comes into your life for a reason. With ''Awake,'' I got to do a drama, and with ''Anger Management,'' that''s my comedy.', 73618, 0), (493634, 'I usually get all my stress and anger out at the gym. But when I get out, I''m kind of a pleasant person - really.', 72239, 0), (493635, 'Through the years I have seen myself as a peaceful person, but the awareness of the anger is part of that process.', 8821, 0), (493636, 'In the final analysis, the incident is seen as originating from an emotional expression of the frustration and anger of the proud people of China who had been subject to ever increasing oppression from without and decadent corruption from within.', 47493, 0), (493637, 'Insurgents have capitalized on popular resentment and anger towards the United States and the Iraqi government to build their own political, financial and military support, and the faith of Iraqi citizens in their new government has been severely undermined.', 71302, 0), (493638, 'Golf courses are beautiful, it''s good for the soul and it gets out the anger... well, if you don''t care about the score then you won''t have a heart attack.', 75933, 0), (493639, 'As with fascism, the rise of Islamic totalitarianism has partly to do with its populist appeal to the class resentments of an economically oppressed population and to anger at political subordination and humiliation.', 17488, 0), (493640, 'Anger is an expensive luxury in which only men of certain income can indulge.', 63782, 0), (493641, 'Be modest, humble, simple. Control your anger.', 68322, 0), (493642, 'I may have been the only candidate in America who failed to ride the wave of anti-establishment anger to victory.', 75934, 0), (493643, 'The reason why I love people, and writing about them, is because they don''t always respond with hate and anger. If they did I wouldn''t have a story to tell. Who wants to know about someone who was brutalised and became brutal? I''m interested in the exceptions.', 7673, 0), (493644, 'You can survive with anger, but you can''t live with it forever.', 51638, 0), (493645, 'As a child growing up in San Francisco in the 1950s, I sometimes met insults when I ventured outside of Chinatown or my neighborhood. I have even been spat on and threatened with a knife. I could have let my anger fester until it became hate. However, I realized they were isolated incidents, and I simply got on with my life.', 23613, 0), (493646, 'Fairest and dearest, your wrath and anger are more heavy than I can bear; but learn that I cannot tell what you wish me to say without sinning against my honour too grievously.', 9910, 0), (493647, 'A wonderful emotion to get things moving when one is stuck is anger. It was anger more than anything else that had set me off, roused me into productivity and creativity.', 65653, 0), (493648, 'The anger that Uncle Junior has comes from my background. My father was the son of an Italian immigrant, and I''ve seen the fire of the Italian temperament. It can be explosive sometimes in ways that are both funny and tragic.', 75935, 0), (493649, 'The American people are smart. They''ve gotten sick of the predictable hyperpartisan talking points and canned anger.', 72504, 0), (493650, 'Having a sweet, wide-eyed, awkward character is more charming and allows for more range. If you come from anger, you''re going to reach a ceiling very quickly.', 74468, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493651, 'I realised one day that men are emotional cripples. We can''t express ourselves emotionally, we can only do it with anger and humour. Emotional stability and expression comes from women.', 74746, 0), (493652, 'The nice thing about anger is that, as an emotion, it''s strong enough to unplug me from the comedian''s mind for a minute and just be a frustrated member of the citizenry.', 71841, 0), (493653, 'Ridicule is the first and last argument of a fool.', 22395, 0), (493654, 'If you lead with the anger, it will turn off the audience. And what I want is the audience to engage with the material and to listen and then to ask questions. I think that ''Ruined'' was very successful at doing that.', 68725, 0), (493655, 'Sometimes with anger you can be much more dangerous than with skill.', 68633, 0), (493656, 'You cannot get ahead while you are getting even.', 75471, 0), (493657, 'The preparation, commitment and desire to win will be no less than the last time I drove a grand prix car in anger.', 75602, 0), (493658, 'It absolutely helped - to write the father in both ''Juicy'' and ''Beasts,'' I had to see the whole story from his point of view. All of a sudden I understood more of what my own father must be going through - the fear, the frustration, the anger... the hope that he''ll leave a legacy.', 75936, 0), (493659, 'The forces that have worked hard to stoke populist anger against reform are the very ones that benefit from a health system which puts profits ahead of quality care for its patients.', 73762, 0), (493660, 'If somebody honks a horn in Cleveland, they''re saying ''Hi.'' It''s so rare to be honked at in anger. When we have merging traffic, we just interweave. There''s real courtesy.', 4102, 0), (493661, 'I think a certain amount of anger has been a fuel of mine, if you want - but also some sort of sadness, and plain mischief, of course.', 68207, 0), (493662, 'Everybody in America is angry about something.', 22871, 0), (493663, 'Us investigators who went out into the field were faced on occasion with a lot of anger, by people saying why has it taken you five or six year to come and see me?', 75937, 0), (493664, 'We suffered a terrible blow on 11 September 2001. We responded with fear and anger. A fight-or-flight response is adaptive in any species. For us, given our power, fight was the only response we could imagine.', 73288, 0), (493665, 'When a man is wrong and won''t admit it, he always gets angry.', 63647, 0), (493666, 'A hungry man is an angry one.', 22374, 0), (493667, 'I was a pretty angry kid, and I got into military history largely as a way to vent my own anger. As I got older it narrowed down to a more specific focus on individual violence. I''m just trying to understand where it came from.', 12788, 0), (493668, 'Most men''s anger about religion is as if two men should quarrel for a lady they neither of them care for.', 67474, 0), (493669, 'I don''t think I could play a character that I couldn''t relate to somehow. I''m not unfamiliar with frustration, anger, shame, helplessness and a load of other emotions that make up our psycho-soup. I try to focus on that frustration, that sense of unfairness, and multiply it.', 75938, 0), (493670, 'Anger is one way to respond to fear. I say one way because responses are categorically multiple.', 949, 0), (493671, 'Man should forget his anger before he lies down to sleep.', 3013, 0), (493672, 'My hope is that out of all the anger and seeming hostility that we hear in some of today''s music will come some sort of coalition that will become politically involved.', 62365, 0), (493673, 'It angers me that a timed, planned and paid smearing campaign is run against me in the press.', 75939, 0), (493674, 'Efforts following 9/11 were important. They set a tone. They reminded those who might be tempted to take out their anger on an entire community that such actions were wrong.', 75940, 0), (493675, 'With Stacy, it was interesting because you know he was within all this chaos, all these different lives that were so broken and so much anger and so much frustration and their skating came out of that, their different styles came out of that.', 20780, 0), (493676, 'An angry player can''t argue with the back of an umpire who is walking away.', 75941, 0), (493677, 'I''m really busted up over this and I''m very, very sorry to those people in the audience, the blacks, the Hispanics, whites - everyone that was there that took the brunt of that anger and hate and rage and how it came through.', 75942, 0), (493678, 'Back in those early days when I began my apprenticeship as a poet, I also tried to voice our anger, spirit of defiance and resistance in a Jamaican poetic idiom.', 68337, 0), (493679, 'Wherever there is injustice, there is anger, and anger is like gasoline - if you spray it around and somebody lights a matchstick, you have an inferno. But anger inside an engine is powerful: it can drive us forward and can get us through dreadful moments and give us power. I learnt this with my discussions with nuclear policy makers.', 75640, 0), (493680, 'Keep your temper. A decision made in anger is never sound.', 67694, 0), (493681, 'I always tell people, anger is like liquid. It''s fluid, it''s like water. You put it in a container and it takes the shape of that container. So many people you see in prison, unleashing war on their people, they are angry, and they take their anger and put it into a violent container.', 7204, 0), (493682, 'For a long time I thought I could deal with my anger and hostility on my own. But I couldn''t. I denied that it had affected me, and yet I was so frantic on the inside with other people: I needed to be constantly reassured.', 75658, 0), (493683, 'Verbally, I''m quite fast on my feet. I could embarrass or anger most people if I wanted to.', 75943, 0), (493684, 'The anger that appears to be building up between the sexes becomes more virulent with every day that passes. And far from women taking the blame... the fact is that men are invariably portrayed as the bad guys. Being a good man is like being a good Nazi.', 72650, 0), (493685, 'The Eyemo was heavy and could be noisy. Once, I was in an auditorium filming a speech made by Goebbels when, suddenly, it decided to emit a huge snarling sound. Goebbels froze, and hundreds of uniformed Brownshirts turned and glared at me in anger. It was not a comfortable moment.', 75944, 0), (493686, 'When trying to start a company, your enemy isn''t criticism, anger or insults. Your enemy is apathy.', 75945, 0), (493687, 'The anger of a person who is strong, can always bide its time.', 7793, 0), (493688, 'I am too weary to listen, too angry to hear.', 42473, 0), (493689, 'It is only with burning anger that we can speak of this attack by counter-revolutionary reactionary elements against the capital of our country, against our people''s democratic order and the power of the working class.', 75946, 0), (493690, 'Fear generates anger, and fear generates violence, and those were part of what built the Saudi state.', 22039, 0), (493691, 'There''s a reason why anger, fear, and hatred are paths to the dark side: they all spring from a single source - the same source as a certain flavor of love. A dangerously sweet, addictive flavor.', 75947, 0), (493692, 'Your anger is a gift.', 71664, 0), (493693, 'The anger in the Brigade against those who fought the Republic in the rear was sharpened by reports of weapons, even tanks, being kept from the front and hidden for treacherous purposes.', 75948, 0), (493694, 'I think that all the anger and cynicism comes from suppressing things that we always wanted.', 75949, 0), (493695, 'Expressing anger is a form of public littering.', 75950, 0), (493696, 'There is not in nature, a thing that makes man so deformed, so beastly, as doth intemperate anger.', 71809, 0), (493697, 'I know I should feel anger at my father for certain things. But since he died when I was 11, I never got to that point.', 72433, 0), (493698, 'My father was my hero, and he died when I was 11. So, I really never experienced the kind of natural teenage rebellion or the anger at him. I never experienced those feelings as a young person.', 72433, 0), (493699, 'I personally do not believe in politics, hatred, or anger in my musical composition.', 75951, 0), (493700, 'As a system of philosophy it is not like the Tower of Babel, so daring its high aim as to seek a shelter against God''s anger; but it is like a pyramid poised on its apex.', 75952, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493701, 'Anger becomes limiting, restricting. You can''t see through it. While anger is there, look at that, too. But after a while, you have to look at something else.', 11682, 0), (493702, 'The anger and the brutality against everything can readily from one hour to the next be transformed into its opposite.', 1801, 0), (493703, 'There''s a difference between an outburst of spontaneous anger, which doesn''t have a political objective, and a more measured response that we saw in the Occupy Wall Street movement.', 16973, 0), (493704, 'Take care of your body. It''s the only place you have to live.', 1295, 0), (493705, 'Physical fitness is not only one of the most important keys to a healthy body, it is the basis of dynamic and creative intellectual activity.', 1680, 0), (493706, 'Fitness is not about being better than someone else... It''s about being better than you used to be.', 66708, 0), (493707, 'True enjoyment comes from activity of the mind and exercise of the body the two are ever united. ', 3896, 0), (493708, 'The mind is the most important part of achieving any fitness goal. Mental change always comes before physical change.', 68550, 0), (493709, 'You need to put what you learn into practice and do it over and over again until it''s a habit. I always say, ''Seeing is not believing. Doing is believing.'' There is a lot to learn about fitness, nutrition and emotions, but once you do, you can master them instead of them mastering you.', 72677, 0), (493710, 'Exercise to stimulate, not to annihilate. The world wasn''t formed in a day, and neither were we. Set small goals and build upon them.', 71197, 0), (493711, 'Swimming is normal for me. I''m relaxed. I''m comfortable, and I know my surroundings. It''s my home.', 30837, 0), (493712, 'Exercise should be regarded as tribute to the heart.', 72984, 0), (493713, 'Number one, like yourself. Number two, you have to eat healthy. And number three, you''ve got to squeeze your buns. That''s my formula.', 68273, 0), (493714, 'Practice puts brains in your muscles.', 44942, 0), (493715, 'Our growing softness, our increasing lack of physical fitness, is a menace to our security.', 1680, 0), (493716, 'You can always improve your fitness if you keep training.', 75953, 0), (493717, 'I don''t smoke, don''t drink much, and go to the gym five times a week. I live a healthy lifestyle and feel great. I can run a marathon, you know.', 70732, 0), (493718, 'Fitness is important, but the most important thing is how you adapt and the way you feel physically. To adapt to a new position. To try to change your game.', 75954, 0), (493719, 'A feeble body weakens the mind.', 1372, 0), (493720, 'The value and utility of any experiment are determined by the fitness of the material to the purpose for which it is used, and thus in the case before us it cannot be immaterial what plants are subjected to experiment and in what manner such experiment is conducted.', 70545, 0), (493721, 'Resting for me is fitness training.', 69222, 0), (493722, 'Fitness needs to be perceived as fun and games or we subconsciously avoid it.', 68389, 0), (493723, 'My wife and I work out together almost every day. It''s just a great way to spend time together. We''re going to run a marathon together later this year, and that''s one more goal that we''ll accomplish as husband and wife.', 66618, 0), (493724, 'In my judgment, physical fitness is basic to all forms of excellence and to a strong, confident nation.', 60667, 0), (493725, 'Sport is not just about entertainment. It is equally about winning and losing, pooling and galvanising the energy of the youth, upgrading people''s physical fitness and mental prowess.', 68086, 0), (493726, 'My fitness journey will be a lifelong journey.', 66708, 0), (493727, 'As a longtime practitioner of yoga and a person who''s been involved in physical fitness my whole life, I can tell you, yoga helps you achieve altered states of consciousness. It is not just stretching. The only way you can say that it''s stretching is if you haven''t done it, or that you haven''t done it rigorously for a long period of time.', 43216, 0), (493728, 'Regularity in the hours of rising and retiring, perseverance in exercise, adaptation of dress to the variations of climate, simple and nutritious aliment, and temperance in all things are necessary branches of the regimen of health.', 68382, 0), (493729, 'Exercise is the chief source of improvement in our faculties.', 64592, 0), (493730, 'I like exercise. I like a healthy body.', 69593, 0), (493731, 'If it weren''t for the fact that the TV set and the refrigerator are so far apart, some of us wouldn''t get any exercise at all.', 22256, 0), (493732, 'I attend to my fitness. I go the gym every day and try to maintain my physical fitness; without that, it is tough to take challenges on the chess board.', 72572, 0), (493733, 'I have never taken any exercise, except sleeping and resting, and I never intend to take any.', 286, 0), (493734, 'You must also give mental and physical fitness priority.', 68718, 0), (493735, 'Promoting healthy lifestyles and encouraging fitness are so important for our children''s development and reducing the nation''s epidemic of childhood obesity.', 67638, 0), (493736, 'I try and groom myself, be it through fitness or dance.', 67036, 0), (493737, 'My weight fluctuates depending on my mood and my current devotion to my fitness routine.', 2250, 0), (493738, 'Don''t get hung up on the size. If you feel bad about yourself because a 12 is what fits, take a Sharpie, and write ''6'' on the label.', 36959, 0), (493739, 'It''s so easy to lose your fitness and so hard to gain it back.', 67841, 0), (493740, 'When the child begins to think and to make use of the written language to express his rudimentary thinking, he is ready for elementary work; and this fitness is a question not of age or other incidental circumstance but of mental maturity.', 11408, 0), (493741, 'I don''t lift weights. I do fitness exercises to stay strong.', 69792, 0), (493742, 'The first time I see a jogger smiling, I''ll consider it.', 17330, 0), (493743, 'Exercise is labor without weariness.', 2087, 0), (493744, 'For exercise, I now run with my chocolate Lab puppy, Oscar.', 72089, 0), (493745, 'I would rather exercise than read a newspaper.', 75955, 0), (493746, 'Like most people I can be lazy, so it''s nice to have a goal or deadline or reason to work out. I feel better when I get to exercise, or when I''m outdoors. I like to hike, swim and run, and I love to play soccer.', 2042, 0), (493747, 'I didn''t have the same fitness or ability as the other girls, so I had to beat them with my mind.', 67177, 0), (493748, 'I think it''s more important to be fit so that you can be healthy and enjoy activities than it is to have a good body.', 75956, 0), (493749, 'It''s challenging, but you have to at least try to eat right and exercise.', 73863, 0), (493750, 'You can''t get rid of it with exercise alone. You can do the most vigorous exercise and only burn up 300 calories in an hour. If you''ve got fat on your body, the exercise firms and tones the muscles. But when you use that tape measure, what makes it bigger? It''s the fat!', 71217, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493751, 'I love to swim for miles I could just go back and forth. ', 69168, 0), (493752, 'What''s important is to get into shape and then not to have to worry about it. I don''t want to get on stage and not being able to do something. Not being physically fit doesn''t work for me.', 49828, 0), (493753, 'My job is to be fit and I''m really blessed that I get to go and work out and live a really healthy lifestyle.', 75957, 0), (493754, 'Fitness is not an option. It''s part of my job.', 68292, 0), (493755, 'No one ceases to be a man, no one forfeits his rights to civilization merely by being more or less uncultured, and since the Filipino is regarded as a fit citizen when he is asked to pay taxes or shed his blood to defend the fatherland, why must this fitness be denied him when the question arises of granting him some right?', 3961, 0), (493756, 'I love fitness, yoga. I love fashion. On the weekends, I try to relax. I have pretty crazy weeks. I like spas and nice dinners. I''m not much of a club person. I like to hang on the beach in Malibu.', 66883, 0), (493757, 'You can be in excellent physical shape, with low cholesterol, a healthy body weight and good overall physical fitness - but that doesn''t necessarily mean you''re healthy.', 69458, 0), (493758, 'The spirit of the Olympic movement is great for young people because it teaches them about the training and discipline required to compete. Even if they don''t make the teams, they can rededicate their lives to the art of sport, discipline, and physical fitness.', 72313, 0), (493759, 'I suffer panic attacks which has made me really conscious about my fitness and I have become addicted to jogging. It might sound odd but a lot of good has come out of it. My fans send letters saying they have taken up jogging because I do it.', 16756, 0), (493760, 'Fitness is a luxury when you are busy!', 153, 0), (493761, 'Never, ever exercise in front of a TV or while reading. You lose 50 percent of the benefit of the exercise by not hearing and feeling your heart rate, your sweat and the pain levels that need to be encountered in fitness training.', 75958, 0), (493762, 'If you ask me about my success story, the secret is I know when to pull myself back. I don''t overexpose myself; I give proper gaps whenever I can. I do not over spend myself, I keep myself busy in lot of activities. I really work hard; I work harder than others, by focussing on my fitness level and studying music.', 71716, 0), (493763, 'I am pleased with the fitness that I have.', 69701, 0), (493764, 'My own preferred fitness regime is to use my bicycle.', 69750, 0), (493765, 'Fitness, defending, the mental stuff - those were all weaknesses of mine. And I turned those into strengths.', 53025, 0), (493766, 'I do a lot of biking. I need that mileage and the long-distance stuff because tennis demands it. My fitness trainer is always trying to convince me to do an Ironman. I can probably run the marathon, I can make the 112 miles on the bike, but I will never swim for 2.4 miles. I will die after 100 meters.', 75959, 0), (493767, 'It takes about four days of virtuous living to create a little weight loss. That also happens to be the time required to get used to eating less. In other words, if you can get past day three of a fitness regimen, things improve.', 29471, 0), (493768, 'I''m quite into fitness, and I have a fantastic personal trainer who knows me, knows my body, knows when to push me, and knows when not to push me. She doesn''t make me do 20 burpees in a row and instead focuses on strengthening my core, telling me we need to focus on making me into ''a tall giraffe''!', 69238, 0), (493769, 'Teaching kids about health and fitness is important to me. It''s about being fit for life.', 63993, 0), (493770, 'People need to have clear goals about why they are exercising, and they should consult a fitness expert to find out what kind of exercise is suitable.', 72611, 0), (493771, 'For me, triathlons were something that was down to me and my fitness. Now, I really enjoy the pain in the triathlon of chasing someone down. It''s a bit like chasing down Nico Rosberg in the last few laps at Silverstone - it makes you feel alive.', 69222, 0), (493772, 'If someone thinks, ''I''ll spend the off season working on my fitness and I''ll come back a better cricketer,'' I don''t think that''s enough. You need to spend a lot of time working on your skills and honing your skills.', 69228, 0), (493773, 'I try to come at fitness and nutrition from a perspective of gentleness and what will make me feel good afterwards. I try to stay out of the mindset of needing to fix myself. I do whatever seems fun to me.', 69267, 0), (493774, 'Muscles come and go flab lasts. ', 5968, 0), (493775, 'I recommend that people try new stuff or take new fitness classes all the time. It''s important to mix up your routine, not only for your body, but also for your mental state.', 68292, 0), (493776, 'I think if you exercise, your state of mind - my state of mind - is usually more at ease, ready for more mental challenges. Once I get the physical stuff out of the way it always seems like I have more calmness and better self-esteem.', 67878, 0), (493777, 'Training is such a vital part of preparation for a game, you really do train to play. It tops up your ability, like sharpening a carving knife. You can get away with not doing it for a while, as long as you have reached a certain standard of fitness.', 72010, 0), (493778, 'Oh, and once, when I was in the Marines, I got a perfect score on my physical fitness test.', 1184, 0), (493779, 'My Daddy liked physical fitness and wanted me to be a prizefighter.', 75960, 0), (493780, 'Cycling keeps me lean and I need to stay in shape, especially as I still like eating chocolate and ice-cream! I like to go mountain biking too. Running is also good; it''s what we were designed to do as humans, so it comes naturally.', 75961, 0), (493781, 'I would like to thank everyone who supported me to be fit for the Euros. I had some fitness problems before the tournament, but I am here now!', 75485, 0), (493782, 'Fitness has always been one of the top priorities in my life because that''s the way I grew up, with soccer being the sport of choice.', 13964, 0), (493783, 'Our children are obese, either have or being threatened by diabetes, high blood pressure, high cholesterol, and not socially adjusting properly to others because of a lack of fitness.', 68273, 0), (493784, 'I can jog, but I can''t run. That''s hard for me. I like the fact that I can jog for fitness, but to me there''s a huge difference between jogging and running.', 72269, 0), (493785, 'For years, I always thought it was hilarious that I was this fitness guru, because fitness was just a tool I utilized to help people improve their confidence. For me, it''s never been about fitness. It''s always been about helping to empower people.', 1860, 0), (493786, 'A drunkard in the gutter is just where he ought to be, according to the fitness and tendency of things. Nature has set upon him the process of decline and dissolution by which she removes things which have survived their usefulness.', 48695, 0), (493787, 'If a man achieves victory over this body, who in the world can exercise power over him? He who rules himself rules over the whole world.', 74086, 0), (493788, 'I''ve exercised with women so thin that buzzards followed them to their cars.', 152, 0), (493789, 'Never hurry. Take plenty of exercise. Always be cheerful. Take all the sleep you need. You may expect to be well.', 17463, 0), (493790, 'Exercise is done against one''s wishes and maintained only because the alternative is worse.', 73296, 0), (493791, 'I wanted to get really fit. I wanted to lose some weight. So I''ve been doing Pilates and yoga, trying to lean out my body so I won''t be bulky.', 70497, 0), (493792, 'What''s wrong with extreme dieting and hard-core fitness plans is that they don''t take into account the rest of your life.', 68292, 0), (493793, 'When you''re singing, you''re using extra muscles, and it requires a lot of exercise and breathing. You can''t do that if you''re a sissy. If I have any fitness advice for people, I''d tell them to sing more. It''s good therapy, too.', 16011, 0), (493794, 'Doing nothing would stress me out. So I am still pretty much active practicing judo with my friends, who are former judo athletes, to maintain our fitness as well as the friendships among us. In my spare time, I usually go jogging around the Gelora Bung Karno stadium or head to the gym.', 75962, 0), (493795, 'People assume that you need to run fast to get to optimum fitness, but the truth is endurance lifting makes you stronger and leaner.', 69739, 0), (493796, 'I would say 90 percent of the stuff we do is technical anyway. If you look at a two-hour training day, 12 minutes are probably spent running or gaining fitness.', 68254, 0), (493797, 'Mental fitness is served by consciously redirecting our attention away from the constant bombardment from the media whose reason to be seems to be focused on keeping us in a state of constant alert.', 45801, 0), (493798, 'In my view, fitness training isn''t that important in England, as they all train with such intensity anyway and have a competitive edge when just sprinting. The matches are all hard-fought, too.', 17409, 0), (493799, 'I do yoga, I do Bikram and I run, and I eat really healthy.', 47, 0), (493800, 'One of the things I''ve always enjoyed is moving around and staying fit. Physicality is such a big part of being an actor, but it''s also about stillness and silence.', 67004, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493801, 'Being a dancer is my metaphor for life because you have to know your body. Being a dancer and paying attention to fitness is all about moving in balance.', 1245, 0), (493802, 'Just as you can''t blindly follow fashion, you can''t follow fitness, either.', 66951, 0), (493803, 'I''m not a fitness model; I''m just a singer. If people focus on that, that''s what I care about.', 68914, 0), (493804, 'I''ve been into exercise my whole life, been a runner and been into health and fitness always.', 66528, 0), (493805, 'I tell my sons all the time, ''The most important thing in your life is fitness,'' but a lot of fighters go overboard.', 26132, 0), (493806, 'I created a fitness club with five friends. We have weekly check-ins and a reward system - and group penalties if one of us slacks off.', 68921, 0), (493807, 'There is a moment when you get older when your metabolism slows down and you don''t feel like working out any more, so you don''t want to keep yourself fit any more, but that''s your decision. Why should you be judged for it?', 47095, 0), (493808, 'I say, ''Use it or lose it.'' I have my own fitness regime, which is centred around stretching, free-weights and fast walking. I also have a trainer half of the year, as I spend my summers in the south of France where I swim a lot.', 50885, 0), (493809, 'My assumption was that people are already motivated to go to a fitness class. That''s who I am. I was already ready to go out there and get to class. All I needed was a search tool. But it turns out people need more than that, and that''s why gym memberships exist.', 68925, 0), (493810, 'Some people have that school of thought where fitness isn''t enjoyable, but we''re making it enjoyable, I think, by making it more fun, challenging, and engaging rather than this boring thing that you have to do. It''s about using technology and data to change this experience.', 68925, 0), (493811, 'The manager and the fitness staff condition every training session. They plan it out week by week on what players need. If players need a rest, they will do that; if players need to work hard, they will do that as well.', 75689, 0), (493812, 'We''ve all tried to bunk our gym session or dance class. A single routine can get monotonous. That''s why I have decided to make my fitness regime fun by incorporating different workouts into my schedule. From dancing to yoga, I plan to keep it as interesting as possible so I''m never bored of working out.', 73844, 0), (493813, 'I understand only three things - films, fitness, and food.', 68929, 0), (493814, 'For fitness, I''ve just bought a watch which keeps a track of how many calories I burn, what''s my heart rate, which is very fascinating.', 67036, 0), (493815, 'All we''re trying to do is change how people think about fitness. And build Under Armour into the biggest brand in the entire land.', 67039, 0), (493816, 'For a while after college, I was thinking of becoming a fitness trainer, and I am a certified aqua trainer.', 69038, 0), (493817, 'When you get into the final week of the Tour de France, it becomes a different kind of race. As the distance and the fatigue really tell, that is when it becomes a proper test of everyone''s fitness.', 66926, 0), (493818, 'I can work hard and be disciplined like a soldier, but I could never reach their level of fitness.', 69193, 0), (493819, 'I try to keep at a non-obsessive level of fitness. It''s not about looking great, it''s about just feeling good. So I do a lot of yoga. Bikram just blows my mind. It''s mental as well as physical; if I don''t train, I get very depressed.', 69193, 0), (493820, 'It''s not like I was trying to be sexy but I had to get fit because I had to be able to do stunts. Also I wanted that, if Bond took his clothes off, he looked like a man who did what he did, which was kill people for a living. I thought the only way to do that was to work out and get fit and buff and get physically into shape.', 66678, 0), (493821, 'When I was back to 100 per cent fitness, I was able to show what I was capable of. I like to think I will bring a freshness into the Euros, and now that I am captain, I am going to do my best to take responsibility.', 67768, 0), (493822, 'At the start of his second term, one wonders less about Obama''s fitness than his willingness: Why doesn''t he do more to build and maintain the relationships required to govern in era of polarization?', 27482, 0), (493823, 'In the British Special Air Service, combat fitness is all about running.', 9272, 0), (493824, 'I never stop working when I''m on stage, and that''s my fitness.', 23445, 0), (493825, 'At my first Olympics, I didn''t have a contract, and I wasn''t making any money. After my first Olympics, I was working at 24 Hour Fitness at the front desk. I would go to practice in the morning, run home, shower, grab some food and then go straight to work. I didn''t get off of work until 10 or 11 o''clock at night.', 75963, 0), (493826, 'I''m French, so I''m quite lazy about exercising, and I smoke. But I do love going for a run in the morning with my dog. That''s all.', 68128, 0), (493827, 'I took up boxing as a fitness thing. I got obsessed, and I would go every day when I wasn''t working. It''s just an insane sport when you get into it.', 72470, 0), (493828, 'For most athletes, there''s a focus on your own fitness, but I have to rely on my horse, too. I''ve been very lucky so far, and it hasn''t presented a problem, but you can never count on a competition going as planned until you''re there and actually doing it.', 68290, 0), (493829, 'I''m not a waif-y girl and never will be. I think it''s healthy when fitness experts encourage fitness rather than getting a certain body shape.', 67671, 0), (493830, 'As Mick Jagger will tell you, performing is an aerobic work-out. I''ve got the bass guitar, which is the heaviest of all the instruments, and I''m a little girl, in boiling-hot leather under the lights. You have to keep the fitness level up if you want to look good up there.', 67772, 0), (493831, 'For much of the year, you''re just trying to maintain your fitness. It''s not often you get a lot of time to really concentrate on improving it.', 68852, 0), (493832, 'My fitness trainer''s English, my physio''s English, some of my friends are English. I don''t have a problem with English people at all.', 68852, 0), (493833, 'Staying more controlled mentally stemmed from taking my fitness more seriously. When you''re doing track work, sprints and so on, it''s pretty painful, but that does make you feel better prepared and therefore mentally stronger when you''re going into a match. You know, without a doubt, that you are strong enough to last.', 68852, 0), (493834, 'Early in my career, I got roles that demanded that I be fit to carry off the angry young man look. Of course, I''m a fitness freak, and that''s something I picked up from my dad.', 72134, 0), (493835, 'While I try to keep my fitness regimen consistent, during awards season, I''m especially conscious of what I''ll be wearing and plan my workouts accordingly.', 11802, 0), (493836, 'I''m doing four hours of gymnastics training a day, six days a week and then an extra two to three hours in a fitness center as well.', 67659, 0), (493837, 'I haven''t always been into fitness. But I noticed that when I''d be on stage playing a show, I could hardly make it through the fifth song without having to take a breather.', 22972, 0), (493838, 'We talk a lot on ''Biggest Loser'' about how fitness is a natural antidepressant, how it burns off stress. What I like about running is that it gives me time alone. I''m always busy, with people at work, with my kids. I love getting out for a run by myself and just listening to my music.', 68292, 0), (493839, 'I have been through various fitness regimes. I used to run about five miles a day and I did aerobics for a while.', 9151, 0), (493840, 'Virat Kohli has so far shown that he has more ability and talent than anybody else, and if he can play till 32 or 34 with same fitness and without injuries, he will come to a point where not even Vivian Richards neither Sachin Tendulkar had such a record.', 69652, 0), (493841, 'Obviously, your family life is the priority, but there''s still other stuff you have to get done in a day. I think the way I make it work is by taking care of myself, and that includes fitness and eating right and all those things, but also by being very organized and punctual.', 18113, 0), (493842, 'I think when you come to Australia you immediately get the sense of fitness and taking care of yourself and being healthy, and it really shows.', 72755, 0), (493843, 'I go to the gym every day. That tends to taper off when I''m at a tournament. During tournaments, I''m not trying to build fitness. I''m simply trying to keep away any kind of tension. I go for long walks to clear my head.', 72572, 0), (493844, 'Even though I''m not a competitive athlete, I have to still maintain things and try to keep myself fit because I am at that age where I need to make sure to get those regular checkups and make sure everything is in tact.', 63993, 0), (493845, 'To hear both critics and defenders talk about the fitness of Judge Sonia Sotomayor for the Supreme Court, you''d think the most successful Supreme Court justices had been warm, collegial consensus-builders. But history tells a different story.', 68675, 0), (493846, 'Too much redesign has to do more with fad and fashion than with fitness and function. It is change for the sake of change. Such redesign is not only unnecessary, it is all too often also retrogressive, leading to things that work less effectively than those they were designed to replace.', 67673, 0), (493847, 'Imagine how many women could excel in science if not for the pernicious myth that science and math are a man''s game. Likewise, fitness isn''t defined by the Arnold Schwarzeneggers of the world.', 68972, 0), (493848, 'Faith can make no appeal to reason or the fitness of things; its appeal is to the Word of God, and whatever is therein revealed, faith accepts as true.', 68973, 0), (493849, 'I can''t eat whatever I want, definitely not. I''m always controlled because I do a lot of fitness and triathlons, not just Formula One, so I always make sure I eat the right things.', 69222, 0), (493850, 'As the proud father of two teens and past Chairman to the Presidents Council on Physical Fitness and Sports, I am committed to educating parents and especially young people on ways to live a long, healthy and active life.', 71197, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493851, 'When I was 10, I asked my parents for a set of weights. I had my Charles Atlas book to go along with that. Every time we went to the grocery store, I''d rush to the magazine area and read the ones with Arnold Schwarzenegger and all those guys on the covers: ''Pumping Iron,'' ''Muscle and Fitness,'' ''Muscle Builder by Joe Weider.''', 71197, 0), (493852, 'Because I take care of my body, it doesn''t look like the body of a woman of my years.', 49634, 0), (493853, 'I have a pretty active presence on social networking sites, and every day there are messages from so many young girls telling me that they are happy B-Town has curvy women like me. I feel you should be happy the way you are. Of course, fitness is important, but not to the extent of obsession!', 67101, 0), (493854, 'Find fitness with fun dancing. It is fun and makes you forget about the dreaded exercise.', 41969, 0), (493855, 'With fitness, I do Bikrams hot yoga. The gym that I have in my building is amazing. I love to do cardio and weights there.', 69370, 0), (493856, 'Kids are starting at such a low base rate in terms of fitness that it''s taking them years to catch up to where people like me started from. Every little bit is making it more difficult for kids to succeed on a world stage.', 68903, 0), (493857, 'I''ve still got a small fitness and conditioning business where I travel round the world doing stuff for individuals and corporations, mainly fitness training.', 68903, 0), (493858, 'The only weights I lift are my dogs.', 69114, 0), (493859, 'I am 5 ft 6 in, and at my peak, my vital statistics were 37-22-35. I didn''t even think about my weight - but now I work hard at keeping healthy. Fortunately, my husband Richie is as much of a fitness buff as I am.', 17556, 0), (493860, 'Bathrooms are, on a square foot basis, the most expensive room in the house to renovate. If you want to test your heart''s fitness, try shopping for simple bathroom faucets. Add in the cost of the required valves, mixers and trims, and you may need reviving when you see the tally!', 74433, 0), (493861, 'Almost 70 per cent of your fitness battle is won the day you realise what your body needs and when. I''ve made my own diets, and I decide for myself what works for me.', 67647, 0), (493862, 'I look at fitness as a necessity in the same way as how you drink water, eat food, one should look at fitness in a dedicated way. People will look fresh and happy. If you are happy, you in a way look fit.', 67647, 0), (493863, 'Fitness is defined differently by everyone, but for me, the most important thing is being healthy. As tennis players, what we do is not the healthiest thing. We almost abuse our bodies.', 66912, 0), (493864, 'Let''s face it: fitness is boring. But it''s critical to be extremely dedicated to whatever you decide to take up to achieve a desired result. There''s no way you are going to get there without dedication, which is the key for me.', 69674, 0), (493865, 'I believe it''s extremely important to include some other type of fitness activity in your training, so cross training will help you to avoid injury when you are dancing.', 68180, 0), (493866, 'I personally love to run outdoor fitness trails. I love the meditative value I get when out alone, challenging myself to run faster and higher.', 68180, 0), (493867, 'At times, you are mentally but not physically prepared; at times, you are physically but not mentally prepared. I would be lying if I said it doesn''t affect your performance. But the sooner you get over it, the better. So you discipline yourself. That is why fitness counts.', 71176, 0), (493868, 'Obviously, when you''re doing fitness work at a club all week and every week, it''s all about specific drills for what you need to do on the pitch. So I''d be doing a different drill to the centre-midfielders. It''s all specifically tailored for me. For example, my drills are high speed. It''s all about trying to break the line with a sharp sprint.', 69377, 0), (493869, 'Fitness has always been one of my strengths. I can do all the long-distance runs. When I was at school and we entered the competitions, I used to do the 100m, 200m, and the 1500m as well, so it''s never just been a pace thing.', 69377, 0), (493870, 'My bottom is so big it''s got its own gravitational field.', 67115, 0), (493871, 'I might do a fitness video. Actually, more of a fatness video.', 71002, 0), (493872, 'With both kids, I started working out again at 16 days postpartum, but I treated myself with kindness, doing mild workouts, because my fitness level was lower.', 63904, 0), (493873, 'My church has a health and fitness ministry to encourage our members to take care of spiritually and physically how could I not? ', 71662, 0), (493874, 'People may say I developed an iron will, but what really happened is that I made myself much fitter. I think an iron will is always supported by fitness.', 70296, 0), (493875, 'I''m enjoying myself this year and for once I''m not chasing my fitness.', 72847, 0), (493876, 'I''m 33 now and I seem to have hit a fitness plane. Shifting the wobbly bits isn''t as easy as it used to be.', 68735, 0), (493877, 'Sometimes fitness is a good thing to have, but you have to recognise that fitness takes you only so far, and skills are the most important thing. Fitness just helps you execute those cricketing skills for longer and more consistently, maybe.', 69228, 0), (493878, 'The bowlers I respected or feared or rated were not the ones who gave me lip or stared at me or abused me. More the ones who, at any stage of the game, when had they had the ball in hand, they were going to be at me, and they were going to have the skill and the fitness and the ability to be aggressive.', 69228, 0), (493879, 'I eat super healthy and I''m super fit. I dabble in every type of fitness. I have a trainer and I go to the gym. I do yoga as well.', 70994, 0), (493880, 'Overall, I think I''m in pretty good shape, but I''m not really someone that is gung-ho or a fitness fanatic.', 72841, 0), (493881, 'I am concentrating on my fitness levels so that I don''t look old.', 71716, 0), (493882, 'I''m very active when I''m not pregnant, but I think fitness should be a natural part of your life, not something you have to force yourself to do.', 74214, 0), (493883, 'I try and maintain a little bit of fitness, man.', 51929, 0), (493884, 'I have a tremendous passion for fitness, I love challenges and I am a very driven guy.', 29646, 0), (493885, 'The public character of every public servant is legitimate subject of discussion, and his fitness or unfitness for office may be fairly canvassed by any person.', 24927, 0), (493886, 'I know some people who are like, ''I love fitness,'' and I feel like if you have to say that, you''re still in the romance stage. I''m in the stage where I''ve been married to it for 60 years, and I don''t think I''ll ever get a divorce.', 68550, 0), (493887, 'Our regular fitness programme means that the race lasting longer than others should not be a problem, but something you have to prepare for in Singapore is ensuring you always keep well-hydrated, as the heat and humidity can easily dehydrate you.', 72710, 0), (493888, 'They both go together you can''t be in front of the camera hosting a fitness television show in front of 75 million households and not have trained 6 days per week year round - in a bikini no less. ', 59643, 0), (493889, 'Fitness of a top-class squash player is very important, and talent only can''t do the job. They have to get training regularly for at least eight hours a day so that they could put some good show in a two-hour match.', 69778, 0), (493890, 'It''s better to train for 4-5 hours a week than to do ten hours one week then nothing for two weeks. It helps your body adapt and also maintains your fitness.', 71098, 0), (493891, 'I think I have just evolved as a person, as a human being. I like fitness. It''s an important part of my everyday life, and I enjoy and endorse a healthy lifestyle.', 67813, 0), (493892, 'When I left EastEnders, I could have earned an absolute fortune from sexy calendars, shoots for lads'' mags, fitness videos and reality shows. But I always turned them down.', 75423, 0), (493893, 'I thought I did well for someone who has been out for 10 or 11 months. Then I was sub against Liverpool and tried to play for the guys and work on my fitness.', 75964, 0), (493894, 'The goodness of a thing created is the perfection of its fitness for the use which it serves. Now that use is either particular or universal.', 74635, 0), (493895, 'On my days off, I like to be outdoors - on my bike or walking the dog or swimming - so it''s important anyone I date is also into fitness.', 71996, 0), (493896, 'A year ago I had a back injury and followed a good nutrition program to help speed up my recovery. I focused on exercise and staying healthy in order to get back out on the ice.', 68093, 0), (493897, 'When I do get time, I like to hike and I take lots of vitamins and powders to keep healthy.', 70099, 0), (493898, 'Once you are over 30, 35 years old, I think everyone should get down to the gym and start moving again.', 73858, 0), (493899, 'The health industry, the fitness industry, was really starting to pick up. This was around the mid 80''s.', 73858, 0), (493900, 'I do a one-hour workout called Drenched, a cardio-boxing fitness routine, Monday through Friday. There are usually between twenty-five and fifty people there - everyone from stay-at-home moms and professional martial artists to teenagers and seniors. They play great dance music. When I can, I take two classes back-to-back.', 71001, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493901, 'I''m freakishly competitive, so I set a date to achieve a certain weight or fitness.', 69783, 0), (493902, 'I have been particularly struck with the overwhelming evidence which is given as to the fitness of the natives of India for high offices and employments.', 73404, 0), (493903, 'I had something to prove and went in the studio and started writing. I got into fitness and style and learned the whole craft. That was when I wrote everything on the album. I put out ''Don''t Ya,'' and it took off.', 71336, 0), (493904, 'I train Monday through Saturday. I usually have fitness training for 90 minutes, then I''m on the tennis court for 3 to 4 hours.', 72843, 0), (493905, 'Beside the brand-ambassador elements of the modern racing driver, the evolution of the athlete has mandated that as drivers, we are very committed to fitness.', 72031, 0), (493906, 'I think a basic level of fitness can help the body cope with all manner of incidents.', 17174, 0), (493907, 'I don''t want to lose my fitness. I''m 45. I have two babies. I''ve got a long way to go and I want to keep in tiptop shape. There''s no magic bullet.', 75965, 0), (493908, 'You can control what you put in your body - 100 percent. You really can control your level of fitness and how your body looks.', 75966, 0), (493909, 'I always knew I''d keep at it with the plodding doggedness that I used to master lump-less gravy and wriggle out of fitness classes; I always knew I''d get a zillion rejection slips. I figured I''d write part time while working various full-time office jobs, and maybe, maybe in my 50s, I''d be able to quit and try writing full time.', 13012, 0), (493910, 'I love to sing. I also had a band during my college days in Saudi Arabia called Thousand Decibels. If not an actor, I would have become a singer. I am very passionate about work. I am a fitness freak: I go to gym before doing my shoot. I also do yoga.', 75339, 0), (493911, 'I grew up watching Salman Khan and Arnold Schwarzenegger, who have always juggled fitness with acting. In real life, I''m a fitness freak. Besides, it is nice to look at an actor who is fit, and if you become a role model, that''s a perk.', 75339, 0), (493912, 'It''s been a long road back to health and fitness for me. I am just glad to have been given the opportunity to do what I love most.', 75967, 0), (493913, 'Once in a while I''ll get moved to do some exercise. It''s something I long for but the biggest problem is bending down and putting my tennis shoes on. Once I go out I''m OK.', 72727, 0), (493914, 'Fitness is a curve. You can be Lance Armstrong, or you can be really out of shape at the opposite end. People enter the curve wherever they are and then they can move up the curve, by better nutrition and better exercise.', 75968, 0), (493915, 'What you want is to rev up your metabolism so that you are burning fat and calories, not preserving fat and calories.', 72729, 0), (493916, 'Beauty connotes humanity. We call a natural object beautiful because we see that its form expresses fitness, the perfect fulfillment of function.', 72395, 0), (493917, 'We''ve got to get people out of their cars, out of those drive-thru windows, get them walking, get them in parks and get them more active.', 71863, 0), (493918, 'For guys who are into fitness, I think it''s important to wear slim-fit stuff that is pretty tight so they can show off the bodies they have been working hard to have. Women are going to appreciate that.', 73198, 0), (493919, 'I have run two Olympic ''A'' standard times over the past 12 months and with the time I ran at the African Championships last week I know my speed and fitness are constantly improving so that I will peak in time for the Olympics.', 72293, 0), (493920, 'It''s not about weight, it''s about fitness, and one component of being fit is to have relatively low body fat, because fat is not very efficient, whereas muscle is.', 73382, 0), (493921, 'I''m really into fitness, so my hobbies are yoga, Pilates, and working out.', 66883, 0), (493922, 'It''s very important to have the right clothing to exercise in. If you throw on an old T-shirt or sweats, it''s not inspiring for your workout.', 74844, 0), (493923, 'I have found a flat on Merseyside and am settling down here. If I can keep playing and get back to full match fitness, I know I have a lot to offer still.', 75969, 0), (493924, 'Dance never really goes away; it just reforms and reinvents, and it''s become more athletic with new connection to fitness and sport. Dance used to have this exclusivity, but not any more.', 75970, 0), (493925, 'I just have to express myself somehow, either through singing, dance or fitness. You get sick of it; you have days where you think you don''t want to do it, but generally after I''ve done something, I feel better. That''s why I do the exercise: to earn my bar of chocolate and cappuccino.', 75970, 0), (493926, 'Every morning, I eat one fat-free yogurt with a sliced peach when peaches are in season, and one thin slice of whole-wheat bread. The same thing. I don''t want to get fat. And I want to keep my fitness.', 68160, 0), (493927, 'You need to eat normally and healthfully, and you need to exercise. I''m so passionate about this because I think people spend their lives not happy in their bodies.', 66664, 0), (493928, 'For a good workout, I go to At One Fitness in North Hollywood, where my trainer, Jon Allsop, puts me through it all. I like it because it''s a small gym and I''ve known the people for a long time. Jon will have me do cross-training where I''ll lift weights, jump rope, throw around a medicine ball and I never get to stop.', 75971, 0), (493929, 'I keep up with everything in terms of health, fitness, nutrition, skin care, hair, nails. Really, everything. I''m an avid reader of every women''s health newsletter from every hospital in the country.', 71889, 0), (493930, 'I became a fitness fiend when I was about 17 or 18.', 75972, 0), (493931, 'Personally, I need a high level of physical fitness in order to feel at ease.', 75973, 0), (493932, 'I''ve had one very bad ankle injury but otherwise I''ve been incredibly lucky with my fitness. I''ve worked hard at it and I''ve always been fit even compared to other players. That sustains you through various parts of your career, but I am 36.', 72010, 0), (493933, 'I''m healthy now. I probably wouldn''t say I''m at my best fitness level and I haven''t played that much lately, but I''m healthy and that''s all that matters.', 71281, 0), (493934, 'The only way for a rich man to be healthy is by exercise and abstinence, to live as if he were poor.', 19164, 0), (493935, 'So I''ve broadened the fitness concept to make it one of moderation and balance.', 71856, 0), (493936, 'Now I say that if you run more than 15 miles a week, it''s for something other than aerobic fitness. Once you pass 15 miles, you do not see much further improvement.', 71856, 0), (493937, 'You gotta have a body.', 75974, 0), (493938, 'I''ve published one book before, and now I''m writing a book of essays and stories about life in Tokyo. And I have one book coming out in May in Germany, about fitness.', 69287, 0), (493939, 'I decided to write ''True Refuge'' during a major dive in my own health. Diagnosed with a genetic disease that affected my mobility, I faced tremendous fear and grief about losing the fitness and physical freedom I loved.', 14256, 0), (493940, 'I''m still very professional about my fitness. I stay in trim as I always did.', 66589, 0), (493941, 'There are similarities between business and sport, in the pressures involved and in the fitness aspect too.', 66589, 0), (493942, 'Yoga''s an amazing release.', 75975, 0), (493943, 'I enjoy going to the Y. I take all the fitness classes that my dad takes; that''s sort of our bonding - anything athletic, anything sports related.', 73445, 0), (493944, 'I have always maintained a high level of fitness, and that is why I am still able to handle the demands of playing in the Premiership. People have always commented on my fitness, and it''s something I pride myself on.', 75976, 0), (493945, 'I was a bit worried coming back to the Premiership from America, but I have been pleased with my form, and the interest I have received has been good for my ego. I have no worries about my fitness, and I am really looking forward to the season starting now.', 75976, 0), (493946, 'Fitness will be a major factor in the first race and I think that will play into the hands of drivers who have been racing recently, rather than people like me who haven''t raced properly for a decade. I''am not one of the favourites to start with.', 75602, 0), (493947, 'I''m an athlete, so I can get up one day and run and it wouldn''t bother me. I don''t get the time because I work for long hours every day. Being constantly on the move itself helps me stay fit. I don''t go to a gym. I use the stairs, not the lift. I''m not into fitness, but I feel I should start, as it''s healthy.', 73883, 0), (493948, 'Ultimately, I''m in the fitness industry. But, I''ve branched out from there quite a bit. I began doing consulting on writing and getting published in magazines in about 2011. Right around that time, I started doing some angel investing and looking to grow my skills and general experience outside of that.', 73884, 0), (493949, 'I think that our culture is doing something to women - let''s say women in their late 30s and 40s and probably even 50s, - where they really are expected to keep this insane level of fitness and youth. I find that just a real waste of women''s lives. I really do think that.', 11808, 0), (493950, 'With fitness, I decided that I wanted to get into shape, and my passion for fitness and a desire to help other people do the same made me decide to do a fitness video. People always tell me they want to work out to my songs, so why not make a fitness DVD.', 75977, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (493951, 'I am not a fitness freak, but I do my regular exercises.', 70478, 0), (493952, 'Football shape is one thing, and then ''futbol'' shape is a completely other thing. It''s a whole other level of fitness that you have to work to maintain.', 69991, 0), (493953, 'Linguistics is a good way of defining the culture of a brand. The vocabulary used by sports and lifestyle brands - running, fitness, training, motorsports - is all about functionality, whereas the vocabulary of the luxury business - handbags, ready-to-wear - is all about the product.', 70153, 0), (493954, 'I am about to get involved with the biggest cancer hospital in Norway. They are building a fitness center to work with patients. I will be a consultant.', 74037, 0), (493955, 'My mom was a professional fitness competitor, so I go into the gym with her. I train with my dad and mother. It''s embarrassing, because she''s really strong.', 73623, 0), (493956, 'The main thing is that it''s nice to see these young people - 9 to 14 years old - take the opportunity to get more involved in their health and fitness. We need more kids to be more active.', 75978, 0), (493957, 'I also meet with city officials, representatives from governors'' offices, really anyone in that sort of position who has shown an interest in youth fitness, to let them know why this sort of program is so important. I give the same message when I speak at conferences.', 75978, 0), (493958, 'Shearer could be at 100 per cent fitness, but not peak fitness.', 67507, 0), (493959, 'At least for soccer players, it comes down to a blend of two types of fitness - your base endurance, which comes from longer distance running, and your speed, which comes from sprint-based workouts.', 66971, 0), (493960, 'My fitness is good. I hope to improve it even further during training.', 75485, 0), (493961, 'When I''m on the road, I''ll break my exercise into a cardio session and a weights session.', 72686, 0), (493962, 'The fitness builds the foundation for me as an actor to have clarity. Fitness has always been the base of where I start off as a performer.', 75979, 0), (493963, 'Don''t get me wrong, I think bikes are terrific. I own several of my own, including a trendy mountain style, and ride them for pleasure and light exercise.', 60516, 0), (493964, 'My husband and I own a CrossFit Gym. Crossfit is perfect for me because it''s always competitive, all the workouts are in a class environment, and it''s different every day. It''s a constantly varied functional fitness workout done with intensity.', 73897, 0), (493965, 'I don''t do very well with extremes of any kind - extreme diets, extreme fitness - so moderation makes a lot of sense, and Hershey''s has really great portion-friendly desserts to help people incorporate treats into their lifestyles so they don''t feel like they''re depriving themselves and are still living a balanced life.', 75980, 0), (493966, 'I''m such a fitness freak that I eat so plain, it''s gross. I have oatmeal in the morning and then I have chicken breasts and vegetables and spinach shakes.', 75981, 0), (493967, 'It is such a great opportunity to be the face of a brand which I remember wearing as a little kid and running around in half-naked. Bonds is now getting very serious about fitness, and their range is amazing. It''s beautiful and comfy.', 75982, 0), (493968, '15 minutes a day! Give me just this and I''ll prove I can make you a new man.', 71207, 0), (493969, 'I concentrate on exercises from the waist down, since that is the laziest part of a woman''s body.', 69628, 0), (493970, 'I love Nautilus and stretching. The results are immediate, and that gives me the motivation to continue.', 75983, 0), (493971, 'One of my assets is my fitness. My fitness around the net and my movement: that''s my defense to the power.', 36111, 0), (493972, 'A vigorous five-mile walk will do more good for an unhappy but otherwise healthy adult than all the 